le=I Like It (Radio Date: 27-06-2018)|accessdate=June 28, 2018|language=Italian}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| United States\n| rowspan=\"2\"|June 28, 2018\n| rowspan=\"4\"|[[12-inch single]]\n| rowspan=\"4\"| Original\n| rowspan=\"2\"|Atlantic\n| rowspan=\"4\"|<ref name=\"vinyl\"/><br/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ebay.com/itm/like/323327609204|title=Cardi B - I Like It 12\" Vinyl Single Pre Order - Limited Edition|website=eBay}}</ref>{{better source|date=July 2019}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|Canada\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|Germany\n| rowspan=\"2\"|July 2, 2018\n| rowspan=\"3\"|Warner Music\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|Switzerland\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|Germany\n| August 24, 2018\n| {{hlist|Digital download|streaming}}\n| German remix\n| <ref name=\"german remix\" />\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{YouTube|U4fErC9skHE|Audio}}\n*{{YouTube|3z92NeR7KWU|AMAs performance}}\n\n{{Cardi B}}\n{{Bad Bunny}}\n{{J Balvin}}\n\n[[Category:2018 songs]]\n[[Category:2018 singles]]\n[[Category:Atlantic Records singles]]\n[[Category:Billboard Dance/Mix Show Airplay number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Billboard Hot 100 number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Cardi B songs]]\n[[Category:Bad Bunny songs]]\n[[Category:J Balvin songs]]\n[[Category:Latin trap songs]]\n[[Category:Multilingual songs]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by J. White Did It]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Cardi B]]\n[[Category:Songs written by J Balvin]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Pardison Fontaine]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Bad Bunny]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Tainy]]\n[[Category:Songs written by J. White Did It]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Klenord Raphael]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Israel]]\n[[Category:Billboard Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs number-one singles]]\n", "text_old": "{{Short description|2018 song by Cardi B, Bad Bunny and J Balvin}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name = I Like It\n| cover = Cardi B, Bad Bunny and J Balvin - I Like It (Single Cover).png\n| alt =\n| type = single\n| artist = [[Cardi B]], [[Bad Bunny]] and [[J Balvin]]\n| album = [[Invasion of Privacy (album)|Invasion of Privacy]]\n| language = {{hlist|English|Spanish}}\n| released = May 25, 2018\n| format = {{hlist|[[Music download|Digital download]]|[[streaming media|streaming]]|[[12-inch single]]}}\n| recorded =\n| studio = \n| genre = [[Latin trap]]<!--Genres are sourced in the \"Production\" section-->\n| length = {{duration|m=4|s=13}}\n| label = [[Atlantic Records|Atlantic]]\n| writer =\n* [[Cardi B|Belcalis Almanzar]]\n* [[Bad Bunny|Benito Ocasio]]\n* [[J Balvin|Jos\u00e9 Osorio]]\n* [[Tony Pab\u00f3n]]\n* [[Jhay Cortez| Jesus Manuel Nieves Cortes]]\n* Manny Rodriguez\n* Benny Bonilla\n* Edgar Machuca\n* Edgar Vargas\n* Klenord Raphael\n* [[Jordan Thorpe]]\n* Luian Malave\n* [[Tainy|Marcos Masis]]\n* Noah Assad\n* Vincent Watson\n* Xavier Vargas\n* [[J. White Did It|Anthony White]]\n| producer =\n* [[J. White Did It]]\n* [[Tainy]]\n* [[Craig Kallman]]\n* Invincible\n| chronology = [[Cardi B]]\n| prev_title = [[Dinero (song)|Dinero]]\n| prev_year = 2018\n| next_title = [[Girls Like You]]\n| next_year = 2018\n| misc = {{Extra chronology\n| artist = [[J Balvin]]\n| type = single\n| prev_title = Estan Pa' M\u00ed\n| prev_year = 2018\n| title = I Like It\n| year = 2018   \n| next_title = Karma\n| next_year = 2018\n}}\n{{Extra chronology\n| artist = [[Bad Bunny]]\n| type = single\n| prev_title = Estamos Clear\n| prev_year = 2018\n| title = I Like It\n| year = 2018\n| next_title = Te Descuid\u00f3\n| next_year = 2018\n}}\n{{External music video|{{YouTube|xTlNMmZKwpA|\"I Like It\"}}}}\n}}\n\"'''I Like It'''\" is a song recorded by rapper [[Cardi B]] with Puerto Rican rapper [[Bad Bunny]] and Colombian singer [[J Balvin]] for her debut studio album ''[[Invasion of Privacy (album)|Invasion of Privacy]]'' (2018). It was released on May 25, 2018 to radio stations through [[Atlantic Records]] as the fourth single from the album. \"I Like It\" is a [[Latin trap]] song that comprises a [[trap music|trap]] beat and [[salsa (music)|salsa]] music. It was written by the three performers along with Jordan Thorpe and Klenord Raphael, while the production was handled by [[J. White Did It]], [[Tainy]], [[Craig Kallman]] and Invincible. The song contains a sample from \"[[I Like It Like That (Pete Rodriguez song)|I Like It Like That]]\", with [[Tony Pab\u00f3n]], Manny Rodriguez, and Benny Bonnilla being credited as co-writers.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8290823/ranking-top-7-songs--cardi-b-invasion-of-privacy|title=Ranking the Top 7 Songs From Cardi B's 'Invasion of Privacy': Critic's Pick|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|last=Saponara|first=Michael|date=April 6, 2018|accessdate=April 6, 2018}}</ref>\n\nWork on the song took from October 2017 to early April 2018. Its music video was filmed in [[Little Havana]], [[Miami]]. The single topped the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]], becoming Cardi B's second number one, the most for a female rapper in the chart's history,<ref name=\"Hot 100 peak\"/> and the first for both Bad Bunny and J Balvin. It also reached the top 10 in Canada, Ireland, New Zealand, Portugal, Slovakia, Spain, Switzerland, and the United Kingdom. ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' staff, ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'', and [[Apple Music]]'s editorial selection ranked it as the best song of the year.<ref name=\"variety apple music\"/> The single was nominated for [[Grammy Award for Record of the Year|Record of the Year]] at the [[61st Annual Grammy Awards]].<ref name=\"grammys\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.grammy.com/grammys/news/2019-grammy-awards-complete-nominations-list |title=2019 GRAMMY Awards: Complete Nominations List |date=December 7, 2018 |work=[[The Recording Academy]] |accessdate=December 7, 2018}}</ref> It became the first song led by a female rapper to surpass [[List of most-streamed songs on Spotify|a billion streams]] on [[Spotify]], also making her the first woman in hip hop with a pair of billion-streamers on the service.<ref>https://www.forbes.com/sites/hughmcintyre/2020/02/13/cardi-b-has-made-history-on-spotify/#4e2355324d4c</ref> \"I Like It\" is the highest-ranked song led by a female rapper on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100 decade-end chart for the 2010s.<ref>https://www.billboard.com/charts/decade-end/hot-100</ref> It was certified [[RIAA certification|octuple platinum]] by the [[Recording Industry Association of America]] (RIAA) in 2019.\n\n==Background==\n{{Quote box\n| quote = We must have gone through so many different version of the mix. We mixed this over and over and over again. We wanted to make sure the low end was right and the clarity was right and the mid range was right, and it had real dynamic range and great stereo separation with the vocals just sitting right in the pocket. After the truly thousandth listen, I'm like, \u201cThis really works. There's nothing more we can do to this to make it better.\n| source = \u2014Kallman in an interview with ''Billboard''.<ref name=\"recording\"/>\n| quoted = true\n| salign = center\n| align = left\n| width = 28%\n| border = 1px\n| fontsize = 90%\n}}\nDuring the recording sessions of ''Invasion of Privacy'', Cardi and her team were listening to beats and song ideas. [[Craig Kallman]] wanted to include a track that pays homage to her Latin heritage and searched among his Latin music collection of records that he used to play when he was a DJ. Decided for Pete Rodriguez's \"[[I Like It Like That (Pete Rodriguez song)|I Like It Like That]]\" and \"Oh That's Nice\", he added J White to the production process. The sample of the former song \"over a very rough instrumental\" and with a Cardi verse on it was sent to musician Edgar Machuca. White and Machuca worked on the production, chopping up the sample and trying to \"make the song sound better and cohesive and beef up the production.\" Cardi re-wrote the [[hook (music)|hook]] a number of times and cut vocals, eventually choosing the chorus she was most comfortable with. The three producers looped the \"I Like It\" part as they felt that was the catchiest part of the sample. Machucha proposed to add Bad Bunny and J Balvin to the track, with both artists contributing with their verses and ideas. [[Tainy]] and Invicible finished working on the production focusing on the instrumentals. Work on the record started in October 2017, and finished in early April 2018.<ref name=\"recording\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/8471835/cardi-b-i-like-it-oral-history |title=Cardi B's 'I Like It': An Oral History of No. 1 Smash's Grueling Seven-Month Gestation |last=LeDonne |first=Rob |date=August 28, 2018 |work=Billboard |accessdate=August 30, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Production==\n\"I Like It\" is a [[Latin trap]] song.<ref>{{cite web|title=Invasion of Privacy AllMusic Review|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/invasion-of-privacy-mw0003166060|website=[[AllMusic]]|last=Yeung|first=Neil Z.|accessdate=April 8, 2018}}</ref> It is a blend of [[trap music|trap]] and [[salsa (music)|salsa]], and samples 1960s [[boogaloo]] song \"[[I Like It Like That (Pete Rodriguez song)|I Like It Like That]]\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2018/apr/06/cardi-b-invasion-of-privacy-album-review |title=Cardi B: Invasion of Privacy review \u2013 Bronx Cinderella grinds her heel into hip-hop sexism |work=[[The Guardian]] |last=Beaumont-Thomas |first=Ben |date=April 6, 2018 |accessdate=April 6, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Levine|first=Nick|title=Cardi B \u2013 'Invasion Of Privacy' Review|url=http://www.nme.com/reviews/album/cardi-b-invasion-of-privacy-review|website=[[NME]]|accessdate=April 9, 2018}}</ref> As noted by a ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' editor, the song is \"heavily indebted to the world of [[Latin hip hop]].\" Bad Bunny raps in English and Spanish, while J Balvin performs in Spanish.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/8292613/cardi-b-bad-bunny-j-balvin-i-like-it-lyrics |title=Cardi B's 'I Like It' With Bad Bunny and J Balvin Goes Beyond Liking Material Things: See Lyrics |last=Fernandez |first=Suzette |date=April 6, 2018 |work=Billboard |access-date=April 14, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/list/8459289/best-songs-of-2018-top-50 |title=The 50 Best Songs of 2018 (So Far): Critics' Picks |date=June 6, 2018 |work=Billboard |accessdate=June 20, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\n\"I Like It\" received positive reviews from critics. Writing for ''[[Rolling Stone]]'', Brittany Spanos deemed it \"the song of the summer\" and commented \"[it] sounds like it was chemically concocted in a mad scientist's lab to be 2018's reigning song of the summer. [...] Everything about this song is perfect for summer: the trap-meets-salsa beat, features from two of reggaeton's biggest stars, a sample of Pete Rodriguez's half-century-old boogaloo hit \"I Like It Like That.\"\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/cardi-b-i-like-it-summer-song-w521547 |title=Cardi B's 'I Like It' Is the Song of the Summer |last=Spanos |first=Brittany |date=June 21, 2018 |work=Rolling Stone |access-date=June 25, 2018}}</ref> In ''[[The Atlantic]]'', Hannah Giorgis also deemed it \"song of the summer\" considering \"[the song] is irresistible because it channels the rapper at her best: when she feels at home.\" She also noted that the verses from both Bad Bunny and J. Balvin \"match Cardi's energy\" and \"add complementary dynamism to the track.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theatlantic.com/entertainment/archive/2018/05/cardi-bs-i-like-it-is-the-song-of-the-summer/561452/ |title=Cardi B\u2019s \u2018I Like It\u2019 Is the Song of the Summer |last=Georgis |first=Hannah |date=May 29, 2018 |work=The Atlantic |access-date=July 27, 2018}}</ref> Neil Z. Yeung of ''[[AllMusic]]'' considered it a \"notable highlight\" of the album.<ref>{{cite web|title=Invasion of Privacy AllMusic Review|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/invasion-of-privacy-mw0003166060|website=[[AllMusic]]|last=Yeung|first=Neil Z.|accessdate=June 25, 2018}}</ref> At the end of the year, ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' opined, \"[the song] will be on summer rotation long past 2018.\"<ref name=\"ew year end\"/> ''Rolling Stone'' staff ranked \"I Like It\" among the best song of the 2010s, deeming it Cardi's \"hugely expansive vision of hip-hop as a multicultural, worldwide block party.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-lists/the-100-best-songs-of-the-2010s-917532/i-like-it-cardi-b-bad-bunny-j-balvin-917553/|title=The 100 Best Songs of the Decade|date=December 23, 2019|website=Rolling Stone}}</ref>\n\n===Accolades===\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\"\n|-\n|+Critics' lists\n! Publication\n! List\n! Rank\n! class=\"unsortable\"| {{Abbr|Ref.|References}}\n|-\n| ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'' \n|Best of 2018\n|{{center|1}}\n| <ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/music/la-et-ms-best-of-2018-songs-20181224-story.html |title=Best of 2018: The 10 (or so) songs that demanded to be replayed |date=December 24, 2018 |work=Los Angeles Times |access-date=December 24, 2018}}</ref> \n|-\n| [[Apple Music]]\n| 2018's Song of the Year (Editorial Selection)\n| {{center|1}}\n| <ref name=\"variety apple music\"/> \n|-\n|''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]''\n|100 Best Songs of 2018\n|{{center|1}}\n| <ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/events/year-in-music-2018/8489483/best-songs-2018-staff-picks |title=Billboard's : Critics' Picks |date=December 11, 2018 |work=Billboard |access-date=December 11, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Consequence of Sound]]'' \n| Top 50 Songs of 2018\n| {{center|4}}\n| <ref>{{Cite news |url=https://consequenceofsound.net/2018/12/top-50-songs-of-2018/6/ |title=Top 50 Songs of 2018 |date=December 11, 2018 |work=Consequence of Sound |accessdate=December 13, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' \n| The 10 Best Songs of 2018\n| {{center|5}}\n| <ref name=\"ew year end\">{{Cite news |url=https://ew.com/music/2018/12/05/the-10-best-songs-of-2018/ |title=The 10 best songs of 2018 |date=December 5, 2018 |work=Entertainment Weekly |accessdate=December 5, 2018}}</ref> \n|-\n|rowspan=2|''[[Rolling Stone]]''\n| 50 Best Songs of 2018\n| {{center|3}}\n| <ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-lists/50-best-songs-of-2018-764204/cardi-b-i-like-it-j-balvin-bad-bunny-764208/ |title=50 Best Songs of 2018 |date=December 14, 2018 |work=Rolling Stone |accessdate=December 14, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| The 100 Best Song of the 2010s\n| {{center|9}}\n| <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-lists/the-100-best-songs-of-the-2010s-917532/i-like-it-cardi-b-bad-bunny-j-balvin-917553/|title=The 100 Best Songs of the Decade|date=December 23, 2019|website=GQ}}</ref>\n|-\n|  [[NPR]] \n| Best Music of 2018\n| {{center|8}}\n| <ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.npr.org/2018/12/05/671206538/the-100-best-songs-of-2018-page-5 |title=Best Music Of 2018 |date=December 5, 2018 |work=NPR |access-date=December 5, 2018}}</ref> \n|-\n|  ''[[The Guardian]]'' \n| The Top 100 Songs of 2018\n| {{center|9}}\n| <ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2018/dec/03/the-top-100-tracks-of-2018-playlist |title=The top 100 songs of 2018 |last1=Beaumont-Thomas |first1=Ben |last2=Snapes |first2=Laura |date=December 3, 2018 |work=The Guardian |accessdate=December 5, 2018}}</ref> \n|-\n| rowspan=2| ''[[The New York Times]]''\n| The 65 Best Songs of 2018 ([[Jon Caramanica]])\n| {{center|1*}}\n| rowspan=2| <ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/12/06/arts/music/best-songs.html |title=The 65 Best Songs of 2018 |last1=Pareles |first1=Jon |last2=Caraminaca |first2=Jon |date=December 6, 2018 |work=The New York Times |accessdate=December 6, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| The 65 Best Songs of 2018 (Jon Pareles)\n| {{center|10}}\n|-\n| ''[[Stereogum]]''\n| The 200 Best Songs of the 2010s\n| {{center|40}}\n| <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.stereogum.com/featured/best-songs-of-the-2010s-list/|title=The 200 Best Songs of the 2010s|website=Stereogum}}</ref>\n|}\n\n<nowiki>*</nowiki> tied with \"[[Estamos Bien]]\", \"[[Mia (Bad Bunny song)|Mia]]\" and \"[[Te Bot\u00e9#Remix|Te Bot\u00e9 (Remix)]]\".\n\n==Commercial performance==\nPrior to its release as a single, the song debuted at number eight on the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]], becoming Cardi B's fifth top-ten entry on the chart and the highest debut of the songs from the album, which all debuted on the Hot 100 during the album's first week of release.<ref name=\"hot 100\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8342063/drake-nice-for-what-hot-100-number-one-debut|title=Drake Dethrones Himself Atop Hot 100, as 'Nice for What' Debuts at No. 1, Replacing 'God's Plan'|work=Billboard|last=Trust|first=Gary|date=April 16, 2018|accessdate=April 17, 2018}}</ref> Bad Bunny and J Balvin earned their first and second top 10s, respectively. Following the release of the single's accompanying music video, the song rose to a new peak of number seven on the chart,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8459097/drake-nice-for-what-sixth-week-hot-100-number-one|title=Drake's 'Nice for What' Tops Hot 100 for 6th Week; Ties Michael Jackson for Solo Male With Second-Most No. 1 Weeks|work=Billboard|last=Trust|first=Gary|date=June 4, 2018|accessdate=June 5, 2018}}</ref> For the chart issue dated June 16, with \"I Like It\" and \"[[Girls Like You]],\" her collaboration with [[Maroon 5]] charting at number four, Cardi B scored two concurrent Hot 100 top-five singles for the second time in 2018.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8460299/post-malone-psycho-no-1-hot-100 |title=Post Malone's 'Psycho' Hits No. 1 on Billboard Hot 100, Maroon 5's 'Girls Like You' Leaps to Top Five |last=Trust |first=Gary |date=June 11, 2018 |work=Billboard |access-date=June 12, 2018}}</ref> It ascended to number two the next week, blocked from the top by [[XXXTentacion]]'s \"[[Sad!]]\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8462525/xxxtentacion-sad-no-1-hot-100|title=XXXTentacion's 'Sad!' Vaults From No. 52 to No. 1 on Billboard Hot 100 Following Rapper/Singer's Death|work=Billboard|last=Trust|first=Gary|date=June 25, 2018|accessdate=June 25, 2018}}</ref> It reached number one in its twelfth week, earning Cardi her second chart-topper, thus making her the first female rapper in history to do so. Bad Bunny and J Balvin scored their first number one.<ref name=\"Hot 100 peak\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8463605/cardi-b-i-like-it-hot-100-number-one-j-balvin-bad-bunny |title=Cardi B Becomes First Female Rapper With Two Billboard Hot 100 No. 1s, as 'I Like It', With Bad Bunny & J Balvin, Follows 'Bodak Yellow' to the Top|work=Billboard|last=Trust|first=Gary|date=July 2, 2018|accessdate=July 2, 2018}}</ref> She also became the first female soloist to reach number one with two songs from a debut album since [[Lady Gaga]], who did it in 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nme.com/news/music/cardi-b-first-female-rapper-two-billboard-number-one-2348996|title=Cardi B Becomes First Female Rapper With Two Billboard Number Ones|work=NME|date=July 2, 2018|accessdate=July 2, 2018}}</ref> \"I Like It\" reached number one on [[Digital Songs]] in its 20th chart week, claiming the sixth-longest wait to the summit since the chart began in 2004.<ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8472354/drake-in-my-feelings-hot-100-number-one-seventh-week|title=Drake's 'In My Feelings' Leads Billboard Hot 100 for Seventh Week, Ariana Grande's 'God Is A Woman' Hits Top 10|magazine=Billboard|first=Trevor|last=Anderson|date=August 27, 2018|accessdate=August 28, 2018}}</ref> It also became Cardi B's second number one song on the [[Radio Songs]] chart.<ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8465547/drake-dethrones-himself-hot-100-in-my-feelings|title=Drake Dethrones Drake Atop Billboard Hot 100 as 'In My Feelings' Replaces 'Nice for What' at No. 1|magazine=Billboard|first=Gary|last=Trust|date=July 16, 2018|accessdate=July 17, 2018}}</ref> Internationally, the single also charted within the top 10 in Canada, Ireland, New Zealand, Portugal, Slovakia, Spain, Switzerland and the United Kingdom. In the United States, I Like It reigned in the charts for 51 weeks, which made Cardi B the first female rapper to have a song chart that long.\n\nCommenting on the single topping the Hot 100, editor Leila Cobo for ''Billboard'' explained its notability, \"it's part of an accelerated spike of Spanish and Spanish-infused songs on the chart [...] This surge can be attributed at least in part to streaming, which has broadened the scope for [[Latin music]] that is still shunned from major mainstream outlets. But it also reflects the times, the moment and the new openness of the world, despite the entrenchment at the border.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/8463929/-i-like-it-hitting-no-1-means-to-latin-music-billboard-chart-cardi-b-j-balvin-bad-bunny |title=The Times Have Changed: What 'I Like It' Hitting No. 1 Means to Latin Music |last=Cobo |first=Leila |date=July 3, 2018 |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |accessdate=July 6, 2018}}</ref>\n\n\"I Like It\" also became the first number one single\u2014and the first Latin trap song in this genre to do so\u2014on the ''Billboard'' [[Dance/Mix Show Airplay]] chart for Cardi B, Bad Bunny, and J Balvin, reaching that summit in its September 1, 2018 issue, benefitting from the support from both the 80 reporting stations (dual Top 40/CHR and Rhythmic outlets who submit their mix show hours or incorporate it in their playlist) and the core full-time Dance/EDM stations, the latter utilizing the remixed Dance versions of the song.<ref>[https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8472951/cardi-b-bad-bunny-j-balvin-earn-first-no-1-dancemix-show-airplay-chart \"Cardi B, Bad Bunny & J Balvin Earn First No. 1 On Dance/Mix Show Airplay Chart With 'I Like It'\"] From Billboard (August 30, 2018)</ref>\n\n\"I Like It\" was the sixth most streamed song of 2018 in [[Apple Music]] globally.<ref name=\"variety apple music\">{{Cite news |url=https://variety.com/2018/digital/news/apple-music-top-100-songs-albums-2018-1203078843/ |title=Apple Music Unveils Its Top 100 Songs and Albums for 2018 |last=Aswad |first=Jem |date=December 3, 2018 |work=Variety |accessdate=December 4, 2018}}</ref> It was also the sixth most streamed in Canada.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/streaming/8488025/drake-apple-music-year-end-music-charts-canada|title=Drake Dominates Apple Music's Year-End Music Charts in Canada|work=[[Billboard magazine|Billboard]]|last=Bliss|first=Karen|date=December 4, 2018|accessdate=December 4, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Music video==\n[[File:I Like It Music Video (Cardi B, Bad Bunny and J Balvin).png|thumb|upright=1|The director wanted Cardi B's location to showcase a \"neighborhood feel,\" J Balvin (''bottom left'') a \"club scene\" with a live band and Bad Bunny (''bottom right'') \"the street hood feel\". Pictured atop, a screenshot of a \"hero shot\" from Cardi.<ref name=\"director interview\"/>]]\nThe song's accompanying [[music video]] was directed by Eif Rivera and filmed in March 2018 in [[Little Havana]], [[Miami]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.miami.com/miami-news/this-miami-nightclub-is-going-to-make-a-cameo-in-cardi-bs-next-music-video-186507/ |title=This Miami nightclub is going to make a cameo in Cardi B's next music video |last=Abravanel |first=Lesley |date=March 30, 2018 |work=[[Miami Herald|Miami.com]] |access-date=April 14, 2018}}</ref> A preview of the clip was featured on [[YouTube Music]]'s announcement video on May 23.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8457563/cardi-b-i-like-it-video-teaser-youtube-music-trailer |title=A Preview of Cardi B's 'I Like It' Video Appears to Be in the YouTube Music Promo Trailer |last=Penrose |first=Nerisha |date=May 23, 2018 |work=Billboard |access-date=June 24, 2018}}</ref> Released on May 29, 2018, the music video opens with Cardi B in a neighborhood, followed by scenes of Bad Bunny in the streets and J Balvin in a club. It also features scenes of the trio performing together.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/watch-cardi-b-j-balvin-bad-bunny-in-new-i-like-it-video-w520836 |title=Watch Cardi B, J Balvin, Bad Bunny Throw Summer Bash in 'I Like It' Video |last=Blistein |first=Jon |date=May 29, 2018 |work=Rolling Stone |access-date=May 29, 2018}}</ref>\n\nDirector Eif Rivera stated in an interview that he was inspired by the movie ''[[I Like It Like That (film)|I Like It Like That]]'' (1994), which opening scene centered in a neighborhood of the [[South Bronx]].<ref name=\"director interview\">{{Cite video |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5gtccOkrX2Q |title=The Making Of Cardi B's \"I Like It\" Video With Eif Rivera |date=June 5, 2018 |publisher=YouTube |author=[[Genius (website)|Genius]] |series=Framework}}</ref>\n\n\"I Like It\" topped [[YouTube]]'s 2018 Songs of the Summer list in the United States, and ranked fifth globally.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/8472810/latin-artists-youtube-top-10-songs-summer-bad-bunny-j-balvin-cardi-b |title=Cardi B, J Balvin, Bad Bunny & More! 5 Latin Songs Rank In YouTube's Top 10 Songs of Summer List |last=Roiz |first=Jessica |date=August 29, 2018 |work=Billboard |accessdate=August 29, 2018}}</ref> As of March 2020, it has received over 1.1 billion views.\n\n==Live performances==\nCardi B, Bad Bunny and J Balvin gave the first live performance of \"I Like It\" at the 2018 [[Coachella Valley Music and Arts Festival|Coachella Music Festival]] during its second weekend, on April 22.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8372658/cardi-b-j-balvin-bad-bunny-i-like-it-coachella-weekend-2-video |title=Watch Cardi B, J Balvin & Bad Bunny Perform 'I Like It' at Coachella Weekend 2 |last=Marzovilla |first=Julia |date=April 23, 2018 |work=Billboard |accessdate=September 26, 2018}}</ref> The trio delivered the first televised performance of the song at the [[American Music Awards of 2018|2018 American Music Awards]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/events/amas/8476996/cardi-b-bad-bunny-j-balvin-will-perform-i-like-it-2018-amas |title=Cardi B, Bad Bunny and J Balvin to Perform 'I Like It' at 2018 American Music Awards |last=Pedrosa |first=Marina |date=September 26, 2018 |work=Billboard |accessdate=September 26, 2018}}</ref> Featuring colorful outfits and visuals, they were accompanied by a live band composed by trumpet and bongo players. Cardi started the performance by lying atop a rotating circular stage; she then ripped off the voluminous tulle and performed a salsa dance. Bad Bunny was wheeled in for his verse in a grocery cart, while J Balvin joined hanging by the DJ booth.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.xxlmag.com/news/2018/10/cardi-b-i-like-it-bad-bunny-j-balvin-2018-american-music-awards/ |title=Cardi B Performs \"I Like It\" at the 2018 AMAs |date=October 9, 2018 |work=XXL |access-date=October 12, 2018}}</ref> The ''Billboard'' article reviewing the ceremony named it the best performance of the night.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/events/amas/8479133/2018-amas-best-moments |title=2018 American Music Awards Performances Ranked |date=October 9, 2018 |work=Billboard |access-date=October 10, 2018}}</ref>\n\nBad Bunny performed the song with [[Shakira]] during the [[Super Bowl LIV halftime show]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cbssports.com/nfl/news/super-bowl-2020-halftime-show-and-set-list-watch-jennifer-lopez-and-shakira-take-the-stage-in-miami/ |title=Super Bowl 2020 halftime show and set list: Watch Jennifer Lopez and Shakira take the stage in Miami |first=Shanna |last=McCarriston |date=February 2, 2020 |magazine=[[CBS Sports]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.si.com/nfl/2020/02/03/super-bowl-liv-halftime-set-list-jennifer-lopez-shakira |title=Super Bowl LIV Halftime Show Setlist: Every Song Jennifer Lopez, Shakira Performed |first=Elizabeth |last=Swinton |date=February 2, 2020 |magazine=[[CBS Sports]]}}</ref>\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"width: 60%;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Ceremony\n! scope=\"col\" | Category\n! scope=\"col\" | Result\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\"| {{Abbr|Ref.|References}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"9\" | 2018\n|[[2018 iHeartRadio Much Music Video Awards|iHeartRadio Much Music Video Awards]]\n| Song of the Summer\n|{{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.iheartradio.ca/news/shawn-mendes-leads-2018-iheartradio-mmvas-nominations-1.4703119 |title=Shawn Mendes Leads 2018 iHeartRadio MMVAs Nominations |last=Kennedy |first=John R. |date=August 1, 2018 |work=iHeartRadio |accessdate=August 1, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[2018 MTV Video Music Awards|MTV Video Music Awards]]\n| [[MTV Video Music Award for Song of Summer|Song of Summer]]\n| {{won}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" |<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/2018-vmas-winners-see-complete-list-1135082/item/video-year-2018-vma-noms-1127258|title=VMAs: Camila Cabello Wins Video of the Year for \"Havana\"; Complete List of Winners|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=August 20, 2018|access-date=August 21, 2018|language=en}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[BreakTudo Awards 2018|BreakTudo Awards]]\n| Video of the Year\n| {{nom}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{Cite web|title= BreakTudo Awards 2018: Demi Lovato, Cardi B e Ta