//www.ebay.com/itm/like/323327609204|title=Cardi B - I Like It 12\" Vinyl Single Pre Order - Limited Edition|website=eBay}}</ref>{{better source|date=July 2019}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|Canada\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|Germany\n| rowspan=\"2\"|July 2, 2018\n| rowspan=\"3\"|Warner Music\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|Switzerland\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|Germany\n| August 24, 2018\n| {{hlist|Digital download|streaming}}\n| German remix\n| <ref name=\"german remix\" />\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{YouTube|U4fErC9skHE|Audio}}\n*{{YouTube|3z92NeR7KWU|AMAs performance}}\n\n{{Cardi B}}\n{{Bad Bunny}}\n{{J Balvin}}\n\n[[Category:2018 songs]]\n[[Category:2018 singles]]\n[[Category:Atlantic Records singles]]\n[[Category:Billboard Dance/Mix Show Airplay number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Billboard Hot 100 number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Cardi B songs]]\n[[Category:Bad Bunny songs]]\n[[Category:J Balvin songs]]\n[[Category:Latin trap songs]]\n[[Category:Multilingual songs]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by J. White Did It]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Cardi B]]\n[[Category:Songs written by J Balvin]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Pardison Fontaine]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Bad Bunny]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Tainy]]\n[[Category:Songs written by J. White Did It]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Klenord Raphael]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Israel]]\n[[Category:Billboard Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs number-one singles]]\n", "name_user": "2a01:e35:2e68:bca0:780d:3f67:dd20:76a6", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/I_Like_It_(Cardi_B,_Bad_Bunny_and_J_Balvin_song)"}
{"title_page": "Please Me", "text_new": "{{Infobox song\n| name       = Please Me\n| type       = single\n| cover      = Cardi B and Bruno Mars - Please Me.png\n| alt        =\n| border     = yes\n| artist     = [[Cardi B]] and [[Bruno Mars]]\n| album      = \n| released   = {{start date|2019|02|15|mf=y}}\n| format     = {{hlist|[[Music download|Digital download]]|[[streaming media|streaming]]}}\n| recorded   = 2018\n| genre      = [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]\n| length     = {{duration|m=3|s=20}}\n| label      = [[Atlantic Records|Atlantic]]\n| writer     = {{hlist|[[Cardi B|Belcalis Almanzar]]|[[Bruno Mars]]|[[James Fauntleroy]]|Jonathan Yip|Ray Romulus|Jeremy Reeves|Ray McCullough II}}\n| producer   = {{hlist|Mars|[[The Stereotypes]]}}\n| chronology = [[Cardi B]]\n| prev_title = [[Twerk (City Girls song)|Twerk]]\n| prev_year  = 2019\n| next_title = [[Clout (Offset song)|Clout]]\n| next_year  = 2019\n| misc       = {{Extra chronology\n| artist     = [[Bruno Mars]]\n| type       = single\n| prev_title = [[Wake Up in the Sky]]\n| prev_year  = 2018\n| title      = Please Me\n| year       = 2019\n| next_title = [[Blow (Ed Sheeran, Chris Stapleton and Bruno Mars song)|Blow]]\n| next_year  = 2019\n}}\n{{External music video|{{Youtube|3y-O-4IL-PU|\"Please Me\"}}\n}}}}\n\n\"'''Please Me'''\" is a song by American rapper [[Cardi B]] and American singer [[Bruno Mars]], released as a single on February 15, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/cardi-b-returns-to-instagram-and-teases-new-track-with-bruno-mars-2447732|title=Cardi B returns to Instagram and teases new track with Bruno Mars|work=[[NME]]|last=Reilly|first=Nick|date=February 14, 2019|accessdate=February 15, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/cardi-b-and-bruno-mars-tease-new-song/|title=Cardi B and Bruno Mars Releasing New Song This Week|website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|last=Bloom|first=Madison|date=February 14, 2019|accessdate=February 15, 2019}}</ref> Produced by Mars and [[The Stereotypes]], \"Please Me\" is a mid-tempo retro groove.<ref name=\"Billboard\">{{cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8498595/cardi-b-bruno-mars-please-me|title=Cardi B and Bruno Mars Share Sexy New Collab 'Please Me': Stream It Now|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=February 15, 2019|accessdate=February 15, 2019}}</ref> It is the artists' second collaboration after the remix of Mars' \"[[Finesse (song)|Finesse]]\" released in January 2018. The single debuted at number five on the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]],<ref name=\"hot 100\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8499857/ariana-grande-7-rings-number-one-hot-100-fifth-week|title=Ariana Grande's '7 Rings' Tops Billboard Hot 100 for Fifth Week, Cardi B & Bruno Mars' 'Please Me' Debuts at No. 5|work=Billboard|last=Trust|first=Gary|date=February 25, 2019|accessdate=February 26, 2019}}</ref> and later reached a peak of number three. The song's accompanying music video was released on March 1, 2019.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8500610/cardi-b-please-me-video-bruno-mars|title=Cardi B & Bruno Mars Take Over an After-Hours Taco Joint in 'Please Me' Video: Watch|last=Saponara|first=Michael |date=March 1, 2019 |work=Billboard |accessdate=March 1, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Background and production==\nCardi B reactivated her [[Instagram]] to announce the collaboration on February 14, having deactivated her profile for a couple of days after receiving criticism online in response to her winning [[Grammy Award for Best Rap Album|Best Rap Album]] at the [[61st Annual Grammy Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/news/cardi-b-instagram-new-song-single-bruno-mars-grammys-invasion-privacy-a8778616.html|title=Cardi B returns to Instagram and announces new single featuring Bruno Mars|last=Shepherd|first=Jack|date=February 14, 2019|work=[[The Independent]]|accessdate=February 15, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.spin.com/2019/02/cardi-b-bruno-mars-please-me/|title=Cardi B & Bruno Mars \u2013 'Please Me'|work=[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]]|last=Gottsegen|first=Will|date=February 15, 2019|accessdate=February 15, 2019}}</ref> Both Cardi and Mars shared the cover art on their respective accounts.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.complex.com/music/2019/02/cardi-b-bruno-mars-new-song-please-me|title=Cardi B and Bruno Mars Reunite on 'Please Me'|work=[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]|last=Espinoza|first=Joshua|date=February 15, 2019|accessdate=February 15, 2019}}</ref>\n\n\"Please Me\" was written by [[Cardi B]], Bruno Mars, [[James Fauntleroy]], Jonathan Yip, Ray Romulus, Jeremy Reeves, and Ray McCullough II. The production and programming was handled by Mars and the latter four, known as [[The Stereotypes]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.axs.com/listen-cardi-b-bruno-mars-regroup-on-new-single-please-me-136832|title=Listen: Cardi B & Bruno Mars regroup on new single 'Please Me'|publisher=[[AXS (company)|AXS]]|last=Villa|first=Lucas|date=February 15, 2019|accessdate=February 19, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Composition==\n\"Please Me\" is a 90's styled [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]] song described as a \"smooth [[slow jam]] with [[Trap music|trap]] stylings\".<ref name=\"NME review\">{{cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/blogs/nme-blogs/cardi-b-flips-slow-jam-script-new-bruno-mars-collab-please-me-2448386|title=Cardi B flips the slow jam script on new Bruno Mars collab 'Please Me'|work=[[NME]]|last=Daly|first=Rhian|date=February 15, 2019|accessdate=February 15, 2019}}</ref><!-- Do not include the other songs listed in the Pitchfork review here. It is NOT saying the song sounds LIKE them, only that Mars is ATTEMPTING to make something like them. -->\n\n==Critical reception==\nRhian Daly of ''[[NME]]'' praised the song by saying that Cardi B \"dominates\" the track as most songs have \"the man calling the shots\", but that with \"Please Me\", Cardi \"snatches control while making sure she's getting what she wants too\". Daly also felt that \"Bruno's silky, begging vocals\" show \"sensual R&B\", as Cardi B's rapping is \"something far more x-rated\". Daly described the single as a \"mix of modern and classic\".<ref name=\"NME review\"/> Writing for ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]'', Michelle Kim criticized the song, saying Mars \"attempts to make his own bump'n'grind anthem\" but that \"his request feels painfully safe and vanilla, like if a bot was programmed to write sexts\". Kim summarized that the song has an \"awkward tempo\" and is \"definitely not sexy enough to be played in the bedroom\".<ref name=\"Pitchfork\">{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/reviews/tracks/please-me/|title=\"Please Me\" by Cardi B / Bruno Mars Review|website=Pitchfork|last=Kim|first=Michelle|date=February 16, 2019|accessdate=February 17, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Music video==\nThe music video premiered on March 1, 2019 on [[YouTube]]. It was directed by Florent Dechard and Mars, and was choreographed by [[Tanisha Scott]], Phil Tayag and also Mars.<ref>https://people.com/music/cardi-b-bruno-mars-please-me-video/</ref><ref>https://www.vibe.com/2019/03/cardi-bruno-mars-please-me-video</ref> In the video, Cardi is wearing a [[Selena]]-inspired look, composed by a purple leather jacket with fringe and a bustier.<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3o8Czd8qNd8</ref> The music video was filmed in [[Los Angeles]].<ref>https://www.idolator.com/7712372/cardi-b-bruno-mars-host-an-after-party-in-their-please-me-video</ref>\n\n==Commercial performance==\nIn the United States, \"Please Me\" debuted at number five on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]], making it Cardi B's seventh top-ten song and Mars' 16th top ten on the chart. It started with 27.9 million streams and debuted at number-one on [[Digital Song Sales]] with 51,000 digital downloads sold, it became Cardi B's third number-one on the latter chart and Mars' ninth.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8499857/ariana-grande-7-rings-number-one-hot-100-fifth-week|title=Ariana Grande's '7 Rings' Tops Billboard Hot 100 for Fifth Week, Cardi B & Bruno Mars' 'Please Me' Debuts at No. 5|last=Trust|first=Gary|work=Billboard|date=February 25, 2019|accessdate=February 26, 2019}}</ref> The song has so far peaked at number three.<ref>https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8501890/jonas-brothers-sucker-no-1-hot-100</ref>\n\n==Live performances==\n\"Please Me\" was first performed live by Cardi B at the [[Houston Livestock Show and Rodeo]] on March 1, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.chron.com/entertainment/rodeo/article/Cardi-B-Houston-Rodeo-13657199.php|title=Cardi B debut sets a RodeoHouston record|last=Guerra|first=Joey|work=[[Houston Chronicle]]|date=March 2, 2019|accessdate=March 2, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Ceremony\n! Category\n! Result\n! {{Abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 2019\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[BET Awards 2019|BET Awards]]\n| [[BET Award for Video of the Year|Video of the Year]]\n| {{nominated}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bet.com/shows/bet-awards/nominees.html|title=  The 2019 BET Awards nominations|date=May 17, 2019 }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[BET Award for Best Collaboration|Best Collaboration]]\n| {{nominated}}\n|-\n| [[2019 MTV Video Music Awards|MTV Video Music Awards]]\n| [[MTV Video Music Award for Best Pop Video|Best Pop]]\n| {{nominated}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/awards/8528388/2019-mtv-vmas-winners-list|title=Here Are All the Winners From the 2019 MTV VMAs|date=August 26, 2019|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=August 31, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n==Credits and personnel==\n===Recording===\n*Mixed at MixStar Studios, [[Virginia Beach, Virginia]]. Mastered at Sterling Sound, New York City.\n\n===Personnel===\n* [[Cardi B]]&nbsp;\u2013 lead vocals, songwriting\n* [[Bruno Mars]]&nbsp;\u2013 lead vocals, songwriting, [[Record producer|production]], guitar, [[guitar synthesizer]], programming\n* [[The Stereotypes]]&nbsp;\u2013 production, programming, songwriting\n* [[James Fauntleroy]]&nbsp;\u2013 songwriting\n* [[1500 or Nothin'|Christopher Brody Brown]]&nbsp;\u2013 guitar, guitar synthesizer\n* [[Mr. TalkBox|Byron \"Mr. Talkbox\" Chambers]]&nbsp;\u2013 additional background vocals\n* [[Charles Moniz]]&nbsp;\u2013 [[Audio engineer|engineering]] \n* Serban Ghenea&nbsp;\u2013 [[Audio mixing (recorded music)|mixing]]\n* Randy Merrill&nbsp;\u2013 [[Audio mastering|mastering]]\n\n==Charts==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n===Weekly charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2019)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Argentina Anglo ([[Monitor Latino]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://charts.monitorlatino.com/top20/Print/argentina/anglo/20190304|work=Monitor Latino|accessdate=July 7, 2019|title=Conoce el Top20 Anglo de Argentina}}</ref>\n| 9\n|-\n{{single chart|Australia|22|artist=Cardi B & Bruno Mars|song=Please Me|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 23, 2019}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Flanders Tip|6|artist=Cardi B & Bruno Mars|song=Please Me|rowheader=true|accessdate=March 30, 2019}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Wallonia Tip|2|artist=Cardi B & Bruno Mars|song=Please Me|rowheader=true|accessdate=March 30, 2019}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Bolivia ([[Monitor Latino]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://charts.monitorlatino.com/top20/Bolivia/General/20190415|title=Bolivia General|language=Spanish|publisher=Monitor Latino|accessdate=July 7, 2019}}</ref>\n| 16\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Brazil ([[Top 100 Brasil]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://charts.crowley.com.br/index.html|title=Ranking: 22/04/2019 - 26/04/2019|publisher=[[Crowley Broadcast Analysis]]|accessdate=July 17, 2019|language=Portuguese}}</ref>