l": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Twerk_(City_Girls_song)"}
{"title_page": "Finesse (song)", "text_new": "\n\n{{good article}}\n{{For|the [[Drake (musician)|Drake]] song|Scorpion (Drake album)}}\n{{short description|2018 single by Bruno Mars featuring Cardi B}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name            = Finesse\n| cover           = Bruno Mars & Cardi B - Finesse.png\n| caption         = \n| artist          = [[Bruno Mars]] featuring [[Cardi B]]\n| type            = single\n| album           = [[24K Magic (album)|24K Magic]]\n| released        = {{start date|2018|01|04}}\n| format          = {{hlist|[[Music download|Digital download]]|[[Streaming media|streaming]]|[[Twelve-inch single|12-inch vinyl]]}}\n| recorded        = 2017\n| genre           = {{hlist|[[New jack swing]]|[[Hip hop soul|hip hop soul]]|[[Funk|funk]]}}\n| length          = {{duration|m=3|s=37}}\n| label           = [[Atlantic Records|Atlantic]]\n| writer          = {{hlist|Bruno Mars|[[Philip Lawrence (songwriter)|Philip Lawrence]]|Christopher Brody Brown|[[James Fauntleroy]]|Johnathan Yip|Ray Romulus|Jeremy Reeves|Ray McCullough II|[[Cardi B|Belcalis Almanzar]]|Klenord Raphael}}\n| producer        = {{hlist|[[The Smeezingtons|Shampoo Press & Curl]]|[[The Stereotypes]]}}\n| chronology      = [[Bruno Mars]]\n| prev_title      = [[Chunky (Bruno Mars song)|Chunky]]\n| prev_year       = 2017\n| next_title      = [[Wake Up in the Sky]]\n| next_year      = 2018\n| misc            = {{Extra chronology\n| artist          = [[Cardi B]]\n| type            = single\n| prev_title      = [[Bartier Cardi]]\n| prev_year       = 2017\n| title           = Finesse\n| year            = 2018\n| next_title      = [[Be Careful (Cardi B song)|Be Careful]]\n| next_year       = 2018\n}}\n{{External music video|{{YouTube|LsoLEjrDogU|\"Finesse (Remix)\"}}\n}}}}\n\n\"'''Finesse'''\" is a song by American singer [[Bruno Mars]] from his third studio album, ''[[24K Magic (album)|24K Magic]]'' (2016). The song was written by Mars, [[Philip Lawrence (songwriter)|Philip Lawrence]], Christopher Brody Brown, [[James Fauntleroy]], Jonathan Yip, Ray Romulus, Jeremy Reeves and Ray McCullough II. The former three produced the it under the name Shampoo Press & Curl, along with the latter four, as [[The Stereotypes]]. The song was composed after a jam session as Mars wanted to recreate the \"[[new jack swing]] sound\". Atlantic Records released a remix version, featuring verses from American rapper [[Cardi B]], as the album's fith and final single on January 4, 2018, to [[Music download|digital download]] and [[Streaming media|streaming services]]. Musically, it is a new jack swing, [[hip hop soul]] and [[funk]] song with a light influence of [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]. The lyrics demonstrate the happiness of being with who one loves and the positive outcome of that for them and others.\n\n\"Finesse\" was well received by [[music journalism|music critics]], who complimented Cardi B's verses, on the remix, and compared them to the old-school [[Hip hop music|hip hop]] flow. Moreover, according to critics, the song evokes the sound of [[Bobby Brown]]'s album ''[[Don't Be Cruel (album)|Don't Be Cruel]]'' (1988), [[Bell Biv DeVoe]]'s track \"[[Poison (Bell Biv DeVoe song)|Poison]]\" (1990), and [[Michael Jackson]]'s \"[[Remember the Time]]\" (1992). The song was a commercial success, peaking at number two in New Zealand, number three in the United States and Canada. Is has also entered the top ten of Australia, Ireland, Netherlands and the United Kingdom. The song was certified four and three times platinum by the [[Recording Industry Association of America]] (RIAA) and [[Australian Recording Industry Association]] (ARIA), respectively. It was also certified platinum by both the [[British Phonographic Industry]] (BPI) and the [[Recorded Music NZ]] (RMNZ).\n\nThe accompanying [[music video]], which was directed by Florent Dechard and Mars, pays homage to the popular [[Fox Broadcasting Company|FOX]] sketch comedy television series ''[[In Living Color]]'' (1990\u20131994). To promote \"Finesse\", Mars and Cardi B performed it at the [[60th Annual Grammy Awards]]. In 2018, the song was included on a medley of hits performed by Cardi B at the iHeart Music Awards and by Kelly Clarkson at the [[Billboard Music Awards|''Billboard'' Music Awards]]. It received several nominations and awards, winning [[American Music Award for Favorite Soul/R&B Song|Favorite Song Soul/R&B]] at the [[2018 American Music Awards]], [[Soul Train Music Award for Best Video of the Year|Video of the Year]] at the [[2018 Soul Train Music Awards]], as well as Best Collaboration at the [[2019 iHeartRadio Music Awards]].\n\n==Background and development==\nIn September 2014, Mars tweeted, \"Now it's time to start writing chapter 3\", hinting he was working on new music. Following the release of the successful [[Mark Ronson]] and Mars' featured single \"[[Uptown Funk]]\" (2014), Mars headed to the studio to record more songs, and said he had no plans to release a new album \"until it's done\". The album was due in March 2016, but Mars' appearance at the Super Bowl halftime show postponed it for several months. At the time, seven songs were already recorded.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/7534116/bruno-mars-third-album-timeline-24k-magic|title=What We Know About The New Bruno Mars Album So Far|last=Redfearn|first=Dominique|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=October 6, 2016|accessdate=June 9, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180429084606/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/7534116/bruno-mars-third-album-timeline-24k-magic|archivedate=April 29, 2018}}</ref>\n\n[[The Stereotypes]] had known Mars and worked with him since 2007, but after he signed a deal with [[Atlantic Records]], in 2009, they did not collaborate very often.<ref name=\"SUDK\">{{cite web|url=http://www.songwriteruniverse.com/stereotypes-producers-interview-2017.htm|title=Hit Writing/Producing Team The Stereotypes Co-Write & Produce Bruno Mars' #1 Hit \"That's What I Like,\" And Receive 3 Grammy Nominations|last=Kawashima|first=Dale|work=Songwriter Universe|date=December 4, 2017|accessdate=June 9, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180710184649/http://www.songwriteruniverse.com/stereotypes-producers-interview-2017.htm|archivedate=July 10, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hitquarters.com/index.php3?page=intrview/opar/intrview_AaronBaySchuck_int.html|title=Interview with Aaron Bay-Schuck|publisher=[[HitQuarters]]|date=December 13, 2010|accessdate=December 14, 2010|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190521053612/http://www.hitquarters.com/index.php3?page=intrview/opar/intrview_AaronBaySchuck_int.html|archivedate=May 21, 2019|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref> In 2015, Jonathan Yip of the team talked with Mars about working together. Mars was already recording ''24K Magic'' and asked for \"some beats\", which Yip sent. Mars later asked for more samples and The Stereotypes sent them, but they never heard back: \"Nothing came of it\", they said.<ref name=\"TFBR\">{{cite web|url=http://www.thefader.com/2018/03/01/stereotypes-interview-bruno-mars-far-east-movement|title=The Stereotypes earned this|last=Russel|first=Bryson Kane|work=[[The Fader]]|date=March 1, 2018|accessdate=June 9, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180710184648/http://www.thefader.com/2018/03/01/stereotypes-interview-bruno-mars-far-east-movement|archivedate=July 10, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"LATGK\">{{cite web|url=http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/music/la-et-ms-hip-hop-gamechangers-the-stereotypes-grammys-201801256-htmlstory.html|title=After losing steam, the Stereotypes almost hung it up\u2014now they are up for producer of the year|last=Kennedy|first=Gerrick D.|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|date=January 26, 2018|accessdate=June 9, 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180126155916/http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/music/la-et-ms-hip-hop-gamechangers-the-stereotypes-grammys-201801256-htmlstory.html|archivedate=January 26, 2018}}</ref> In June 2016, Yip contacted Mars, who asked the former if The Stereotypes would like to help him finish a song for his album; he needed another song with a certain tempo and key.<ref name=\"TFBR\"/><ref name=\"LATGK\"/><ref name=\"NYTJC\">{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/01/24/arts/music/stereotypes-bruno-mars-grammy-awards.html|title=Meet the Stereotypes, the Guys Who Help Give Bruno Mars His Bounce|last=Coscarelli|first=Joe|work=[[The New York Times]]|date=January 24, 2018|accessdate=June 9, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180613010506/https://www.nytimes.com/2018/01/24/arts/music/stereotypes-bruno-mars-grammy-awards.html|archivedate=June 13, 2018}}</ref> Yip sent Mars an idea that caught his attention, with him asking The Stereotypes to go to the studio.<ref name=\"SUDK\"/><ref name=\"TFBR\"/><ref name=\"IdolMW\">{{cite web|url=https://www.idolator.com/7673678/stereotypes-interview-grammys-k-pop-bruno-mars|title=The Stereotypes Talk Grammy Nominations, K-Pop & Bruno Mars: Interview|last=Wass|first=Mike|publisher=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]|date=January 16, 2018|accessdate=June 9, 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180117021332/https://www.idolator.com/7673678/stereotypes-interview-grammys-k-pop-bruno-mars|archivedate=January 17, 2018}}</ref> After helping Mars finish \"[[24K Magic (song)|24K Magic]]\" and \"[[That's What I Like (Bruno Mars song)|That's What I Like]]\", the team brought \"in another track idea\".<ref name=\"SUDK\"/><ref name=\"IdolMW\"/> The idea went into fruition when Mars decided to come up with the \"[[new jack swing]] sound of [[Keith Sweat]] and [[Bobby Brown]]\".<ref name=\"SUDK\"/><ref name=\"NYTJC\"/><ref name=\"IdolMW\"/> It was created from scratch after a jam session in Mars' studio. While he was playing a drum set, everyone was either playing an instrument, singing, or yelling.<ref name=\"NYTJC\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/grammys/8096383/the-stereotypes-interview-bruno-mars-24k-magic-grammy-nominations-thats-what-i-like-producers|title=Producers The Stereotypes Talk Helping Bruno Mars Find the Right 'Bounce' For '24K Magic' & Earning Three Grammy Nods|last=Weatherby|first=Taylor|work=Billboard|date=January 26, 2018|accessdate=September 19, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181103220457/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/grammys/8096383/the-stereotypes-interview-bruno-mars-24k-magic-grammy-nominations-thats-what-i-like-producers|archive-date=November 3, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nDuring an interview with ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' magazine, Mars said one iteration of \"Finesse\" had him singing about \"gold chains and cognac over a silky beat\", which he found \"too corny\", and another version sounded \"like a Seventies cop show\u2014like I should be on roller skates\". Mars explained, \"Anytime you see us, on tour, on TV, I want to be moving ... I was very conscious on this album of the bounce.\" However, he was not satisfied with the 20th version of the song, rearranging its groove. At that time, Mars also decided to fix the bridge of the song, since there was something bothering him on the harmonies or on the chord progression. Mars furthered, \"I don't know what's not hitting home. There's just something weird that I ain't fucking with yet.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/features/life-on-planet-mars-w447916|title=Bruno Mars: The Private Anxiety of a Pop Perfectionist|last=Eells|first=Josh|website=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=November 2, 2016|accessdate=November 2, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161103014403/http://www.rollingstone.com/music/features/life-on-planet-mars-w447916|archive-date=November 3, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nWhen Mars chose \"Finesse\" as a single, he told The Stereotypes that he wanted rapper Cardi B to feature on it.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://theknockturnal.com/stereotypes-jeremy-reeves-ray-charles-mccullough-ii-talk-grammy-nominations/|title=Stereotypes' Jeremy Reeves & Ray Charles McCullough II Talk Grammy Nominations|author=Staff|work=The Knockturnal|date=January 28, 2018|accessdate=September 19, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190620194904/https://theknockturnal.com/stereotypes-jeremy-reeves-ray-charles-mccullough-ii-talk-grammy-nominations/|archive-date=June 20, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The former said on an Instagram post, \"I met Cardi B at 3 a.m. after my show in LA, backstage, where we recorded her verse for 'Finesse'. She walked in the room and she was everything I'd hoped she'd be.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8092682/bruno-mars-cardi-b-instagram|title=Bruno Mars Thanks 'The One & Only' Cardi B for 'Finesse (Remix)' Collab|last=Aniftos|first=Rania|work=Billboard|date=January 4, 2018|accessdate=September 19, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190831132332/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8092682/bruno-mars-cardi-b-instagram|archive-date=August 31, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Charles Moniz]], Mars' audio engineer, confirmed this as he recorded their vocals on selected microphones and \"brought all the sound elements together\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nationalpost.com/pmn/entertainment-pmn/grammy-winning-canadian-sound-engineer-on-finding-gold-with-bruno-mars|title=Grammy-winning Canadian sound engineer on finding gold with Bruno Mars|last=Friend|first=David|work=[[National Post]]|date=January 25, 2018|accessdate=September 20, 2019}}</ref> Rumors regarding the collaboration between Mars and Cardi B began on Twitter around Christmas 2017. ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]''{{'s}} associated director of charts and radio confirmed Mars was set to release new music on January 4, 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eonline.com/news/903512/bruno-mars-and-cardi-b-collaborate-on-finesse-remix|title=Bruno Mars and Cardi B Collaborate on \"Finesse\" Remix|last=Heller|first=Corinne|work=[[E! News]]|date=January 3, 2018|accessdate=September 19, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190831132333/https://www.eonline.com/news/903512/bruno-mars-and-cardi-b-collaborate-on-finesse-remix|archive-date=August 31, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Production and release==\n\"Finesse\" was written by Mars, [[Philip Lawrence (songwriter)|Philip Lawrence]], Christopher Brody Brown, [[James Fauntleroy]], Yip, Ray Romulus, Jeremy Reeves and Ray McCullough II. Its production was handled by the former three under their alias Shampoo Press & Curl, along with the latter four as The Stereotypes. Mars, Lawrence, Brown, and Fauntleroy served as the song's background vocalists. The recording was done and engineered by [[Charles Moniz]], with additional engineering assistance by Jacob Dennis, at Glenwood Place Studios in [[Burbank, California]]. It was mixed at MixStar Studios in [[Virginia Beach, Virginia|Virginia Beach]] by Serban Ghenea, with John Hanes serving as the mixing engineer. [[Tom Coyne (music engineer)|Tom Coyne]] mastered the track at [[Sterling Sound]].<ref name=\"24KM Notes\"/> The remix version features additional songwriting by Cardi B and Klenord Raphael, as well as new mastering by Randy Merrill at Sterling Sound.<ref name=\"Vynil\"/><ref name=\"ASCAP\"/>\n\nIn early January 2018, Mars announced via Instagram that \"Finesse\" would be the album's fifth single, and unlike the original, the single version features rap verses from [[Cardi B]]. The announcement was accompanied with the single's artwork, which features Mars and Cardi B \"channeling some serious '90s music video vibes\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8085987/bruno-mars-cardi-b-song-finesse|title=Bruno Mars Teases New Cardi B Team-Up \"Finesse\"|last=Branca|first=Nina|work=Billboard|date=January 3, 2018|accessdate=January 3, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180104060737/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8085987/bruno-mars-cardi-b-song-finesse|archive-date=January 4, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.axs.com/bruno-mars-and-cardi-b-throwback-to-the-90s-in-finesse-music-video-126927|title=Bruno Mars and Cardi B throwback to the '90s in \"Finesse\" music video|last=Villa|first=Lucas|publisher=[[AXS (company)|AXS]]|date=January 4, 2018|accessdate=August 31, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190831104301/https://www.axs.com/bruno-mars-and-cardi-b-throwback-to-the-90s-in-finesse-music-video-126927|archive-date=August 31, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> It was released on January 4, 2018, via [[music download|digital download]] and [[Streaming media|streaming services]] in various countries via Atlantic Records.<ref name=\"PDI\"/> [[Warner Music Group]] also released the track to be added to Italian [[contemporary hit radio]] on January 8, 2018.<ref name=\"ItalyCHR\"/> Subsequently, the song was released to US and UK contemporary hit radio stations on January 9, 2018, and January 12, 2018, respectively, by Atlantic Records.<ref name=\"CHR US\"/><ref name=\"CHR UK\"/> American [[urban contemporary]] radio stations began adding the track onto their playlists on January 16, 2018, through the latter label.<ref name=\"UC US\"/> The version with Cardi B was later included on the deluxe version of ''24K Magic''.<ref name=\"24KMD Notes\">{{cite AV media notes|title=24K Magic Deluxe edition (Bluray+CD)|year=2018|type=CD booklet|publisher=Atlantic Records|id=756-78657-56|location=Europe}}</ref> In the same year, a vinyl featuring the remix of \"Finesse\" and its original version was released.<ref name=\"Vynil\"/>\n\n==Composition==\n{{Listen\n |filename     = Bruno_Mars_-_Finesse.ogg \n |title        = \"Finesse\"\n |description  = A 19-second sample of \"Finesse\" containing harmonic background vocals on the chorus.\n |pos          = left\n}}\n\n\"Finesse\" is a new jack swing, funk and hip-hop soul song with a light influence of [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]].<ref name=\"LATGK\"/><ref name=\"XXLNM\">{{cite web|url=http://www.xxlmag.com/news/2018/01/cardi-b-to-join-bruno-mars-finesse-remix/|title=Cardi B To Join Bruno Mars For \"Finesse\" Remix|last=Mojica|first=Nick|work=[[XXL (magazine)|XXL]]|date=January 3, 2018|accessdate=November 2, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190620132321/https://www.xxlmag.com/news/2018/01/cardi-b-to-join-bruno-mars-finesse-remix/|archive-date=June 20, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"RSAL\">{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/see-bruno-mars-cardi-bs-in-living-color-dedicated-finesse-video-205887/|title=See Bruno Mars, Cardi B's \"In Living Color\"-Dedicated \"Finesse\" Video|last=Legaspi|first=Althea|work=Rolling Stone|date=January 4, 2018|accessdate=November 2, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190620132332/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/see-bruno-mars-cardi-bs-in-living-color-dedicated-finesse-video-205887/|archive-date=June 20, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The song draws it main inspiration from the early 1990s new jack swing sound.<ref name=\"XXLNM\"/><ref name=\"AXSLV\">{{cite web|url=https://www.axs.com/bruno-mars-and-cardi-b-throwback-to-the-90s-in-finesse-music-video-126927|title=Bruno Mars and Cardi B throwback to the '90s in 'Finesse' music video|last=Villa|first=Lucas|publisher=AXS|date=January 4, 2018|accessdate=November 3, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190831104301/https://www.axs.com/bruno-mars-and-cardi-b-throwback-to-the-90s-in-finesse-music-video-126927|archive-date=August 31, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The original version was composed in the key of [[A-flat major]] at a [[Time signature|tempo]] of 124 beats per minute. Mars' vocal range spans from E<sub>4</sub> to D<sub>6</sub>.<ref name=\"Original\">{{cite web|url=https://www.musicnotes.com/sheetmusic/mtd.asp?ppn=MN0173346|title=Bruno Mars \"Finesse\" Sheet Music in A-flat major|publisher=Musicnotes|accessdate=November 3, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330145623/https://www.musicnotes.com/sheetmusic/mtd.asp?ppn=MN0173346|archive-date=March 30, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The song features Mars in the center of the track, with a \"tightly clipped vocal delivery\" sounding like [[Bobby Brown]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://consequenceofsound.net/2016/11/album-review-bruno-mars-24k-magic/|title=Bruno Mars \u2013 24K Magic: Album Review|first=Karen|last=Gwee|work=[[Consequence of Sound]]|date=November 22, 2016|accessdate=November 24, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161123201653/http://consequenceofsound.net/2016/11/album-review-bruno-mars-24k-magic/|archive-date=November 23, 2016|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"IPP\">{{cite web|url=http://www.idolator.com/7651802/bruno-mars-24k-magic-album-review?|title=Bruno Mars' '24K Magic': Album Review|last=Bowman|first=Patrick|publisher=Idolator|date=November 21, 2016|accessdate=October 7, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180616153605/http://www.idolator.com/7651802/bruno-mars-24k-magic-album-review|archive-date=June 16, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"BBAU\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/7581423/bruno-mars-24k-magic-artists-influences-riyl|title=Bruno Mars' '24K Magic': A Track-by-Track Guide|last=Unterberger|first=Andrew|work=Billboard|date=November 19, 2016|accessdate=June 12, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180702031704/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/7581423/bruno-mars-24k-magic-artists-influences-riyl|archivedate=July 2, 2018}}</ref> Its instrumentation features walloping clattering [[drum machine]] rhythms, syncopated rhythms, lurching \"orchestral-stab\" synthesizers, and \"close-harmony background vocals\".<ref name=\"ITDN\">{{cite web|url=https://www.irishtimes.com/culture/music/retro-r-b-why-pop-is-getting-jiggy-with-the-1990s-1.3435159|title=Retro R&B: Why pop is getting jiggy with the 1990s|last=Van Nguyen|first=Dean|website=[[The Irish Times]]|date=March 26, 2018|accessdate=May 29, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180622032518/https://www.irishtimes.com/culture/music/retro-r-b-why-pop-is-getting-jiggy-with-the-1990s-1.3435159|archive-date=June 22, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"BBAU\"/><ref name=\"NYTJR\">{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2018/03/08/magazine/25-songs-future-of-music.html#/bruno-mars|title=25 Songs That Tell Us Where Music is Going|last=Rosen|first=Jody|work=The New York Times|date=March 8, 2018|accessdate=October 7, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191004203415/https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2018/03/08/magazine/25-songs-future-of-music.html#/bruno-mars|archivedate=October 4, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> It all resonates with the sound of Bobby Brown's album ''[[Don't Be Cruel (album)|Don't Be Cruel]]'' (1988) and its [[Don't Be Cruel (Bobby Brown song)|title track]].<ref name=\"BBAU\"/><ref name=\"NYTJR\"/><ref name=\"NYTJCF\">{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/11/23/arts/music/bruno-mars-24k-magic-review.html|title=Review: Bruno Mars Delivers Decades of Funk in '24K Magic'|last=Caramanica|first=Jon|work=The New York Times|date=November 23, 2016|accessdate=January 6, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161123221016/https://www.nytimes.com/2016/11/23/arts/music/bruno-mars-24k-magic-review.html|archive-date=November 23, 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> Most critics say the open \"programmed snare line\" on \"Finesse\" resembles the one in [[Bell Biv DeVoe]]'s \"[[Poison (Bell Biv DeVoe song)|Poison]]\" (1990).<ref name=\"IPP\"/><ref name=\"SSZH\">{{cite web|url=https://www.slantmagazine.com/music/the-25-best-singles-of-2018/3/|title=The 25 Best Singles of 2018|work=[[Slant Magazine]]|date=December 10, 2018|accessdate=October 7, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190408060614/https://www.slantmagazine.com/music/the-25-best-singles-of-2018/3/|archive-date=April 8, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/albumreviews/review-bruno-mars-24k-magic-w451090|title=Review: Bruno Mars' '24k Magic' Is a Lush Nineties Throwback|first=Christopher|last=R. Weingarten|work=Rolling Stone|date=November 18, 2016|accessdate=November 19, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161120040607/http://www.rollingstone.com/music/albumreviews/review-bruno-mars-24k-magic-w451090|archive-date=November 20, 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> Its bass line and beat have also been compared to [[Michael Jackson]]'s \"[[Remember the Time]]\" (1992), and the new jack swing style to Jackson's album ''[[Dangerous (Michael Jackson album)|Dangerous]]'' (1991).<ref name=\"NYTJR\"/><ref name=\"ITDN\"/><ref name=\"XXLPB\">{{cite web|url=http://www.xxlmag.com/video/2018/01/cardi-b-bruno-mars-finesse-remix-video-in-living-color/|title=Cardi B Joins Bruno Mars for ''Finesse (Remix)'' Video|last=Barry|first=Peter|work=XXL|date=January 4, 2018|accessdate=May 29, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180530071720/http://www.xxlmag.com/video/2018/01/cardi-b-bruno-mars-finesse-remix-video-in-living-color/|archive-date=May 30, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> The lyrics demonstrate the happiness of being with who one loves and the positive outcome of that for them and others.<ref name=\"RSAL\"/>\n\nFor its single release, the composition of the song was reworked to feature verses from Cardi B. The key of the song was changed to [[A-flat minor]] and the tempo reduced to 100 beats per minute.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.musicnotes.com/sheetmusic/mtd.asp?ppn=MN0184984|title=Bruno Mars feat. Cardi B \"Finesse\" Sheet Music in A-flat minot|publisher=Musicnotes|accessdate=November 3, 2019}}</ref> Her flow and rhymes on the track have been compared to \"turn-of-the-1990s cadence\", as well as to [[Salt-N-Pepa]] and [[Heavy D]] styles.<ref name=\"AXSLV\"/><ref name=\"NYTJR\"/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/01/05/arts/music/playlist-justin-timberlake-bruno-mars-kendrick-lamar.html?|title=The Playlist: Justin Timberlake Stays Funky (For Now), and 9 More New Songs|work=The New York Times|date=January 5, 2018|last1=Pareles|first1=Jon|last2=Caramanica|first2= Jon|last3=Russonello|first3=Giovanni|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180106074328/https://www.nytimes.com/2018/01/05/arts/music/playlist-justin-timberlake-bruno-mars-kendrick-lamar.html|archive-date=January 6, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\nThe album version of \"Finesse\" has received generally positive reviews from [[music journalism|music critics]]. Caroline Sullivan from ''[[The Guardian]]'' praised the song for paying homage to new jack swing, calling it a \"resurrection\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2016/nov/24/bruno-mars-24k-magic-review-barry-manilow-atlantic|title=Bruno Mars: 24K Magic review \u2013 Barry Manilow in 90s R&B clothing|first=Caroline|last=Sullivan|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=November 24, 2016|accessdate=November 24, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161125060853/https://www.theguardian.com/music/2016/nov/24/bruno-mars-24k-magic-review-barry-manilow-atlantic|archive-date=November 25, 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> Nick Levine, writing for ''[[NME]]'', thought the song is \"pitch-perfect pastiche of the new jack swing sound that recalls\" Jackson's \"Remember The Time\" (1992).<ref name=\"NMENL\">{{cite web|url=http://www.nme.com/reviews/album/bruno-mars-24k-magic|title=Bruno Mars \u2013 24K Magic Review|last=Levine|first=Nick|work=[[NME]]|date=December 1, 2016|accessdate=April 21, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170422041240/http://www.nme.com/reviews/album/bruno-mars-24k-magic|archive-date=April 22, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> [[AllMusic]]'s Andy Kellman said \"Finesse\" reminded him of \"the era when [[Teddy Riley]], [[Dave Hall (record producer)|Dave 'Jam' Hall]], and [[Dr. Freeze]] fused hip-hop with electronic post-disco R&B pioneered by [[Leon Sylvers III]], [[Kashif]], and [[Jimmy Jam and Terry Lewis]]\". He added that the song, just like his preceders, \"is a blast\".<ref name=\"AllMusic\">{{cite web|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/24k-magic-mw0002988686|title=24K Magic \u2013 Bruno Mars|first=Andy|last=Kellman|publisher=[[AllMusic]]|accessdate=November 19, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161119045343/http://www.allmusic.com/album/24k-magic-mw0002988686|archive-date=November 19, 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> Patrick Ryan of ''[[USA Today]]'' recommended the casual reader to download the song.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/music/2016/11/18/bruno-mars-24k-magic-album-review/93794880/|title=Review: Bruno Mars makes 'Magic' on throwback third album|last=Ryan|first=Patrick|work=[[USA Today]]|date=November 18, 2016|accessdate=November 19, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161118234215/http://www.usatoday.com/story/life/music/2016/11/18/bruno-mars-24k-magic-album-review/93794880/|archive-date=November 18, 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> On the other hand, Jonathan Wroble of ''[[Slant Magazine]]'' criticized the song for being a copycat of Bell Biv DeVoe's \"Poison\" (1990) and for \"failing to add anything new to his rehashing of new jack swing\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.slantmagazine.com/music/review/bruno-mars-24k-magic|title=Bruno Mars: 24K Magic - Album Review|last=Wroble|first=Jonathan|work=Slant Magazine|date=November 17, 2016|accessdate=November 19, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161119125845/http://www.slantmagazine.com/music/review/bruno-mars-24k-magic|archive-date=November 19, 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> American singer-songwriter [[Meshell Ndegeocello]] accused Mars of copying Bell Biv DeVoe, [[Babyface (musician)|Babyface]] and the work of [[Jimmy Jam & Terry Lewis]] with [[The Human League]] and using it on \"Finesse\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8232751/meshell-ndegeocello-ventriloquism|title=Meshell Ndegeocello Talks Revisiting R&B Gems for Covers Album & Why Bruno Mars Is 'Karaoke'|last=Hart|first=Ron|work=Billboard|date=March 6, 2018|accessdate=November 3, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180918203056/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8232751/meshell-ndegeocello-ventriloquism|archive-date=September 18, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe remix also received positive reviews from music critics. Chris Gayomali writing for ''[[GQ]]'' considered the album version to be a \"sleeper jam\" and dubbed the remix a \"bop\". Gayomali continued, \"The pairing with Bardi hits all the feel-good throwback notes.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gq.com/story/finesse-remix-bruno-mars-cardi-b|title=The \"Finesse\" Remix Is Proof That Bruno Mars Should Remake All His Songs with Cardi B|last=Gayomali|first=Chris|work=[[GQ]]|date=January 4, 2018|accessdate=October 7, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190607121949/https://www.gq.com/story/finesse-remix-bruno-mars-cardi-b|archive-date=June 7, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Dean Nguyen from ''[[The Irish Times]]'' said the remix is a \"2018 single-of-the-year candidate\" as its composition recalls \"Bell Biv DeVoe and ''Dangerous'' (1991)-era Michael Jackson\".<ref name=\"ITDN\"/> Ron Dicker of ''[[HuffPost]]'' complemented the duo and the song, \"Mars and Cardi B killed it in a remix for the ages.\"<ref name=\"HPRD\">{{cite web|url=https://www.huffpost.com/entry/bruno-mars-cardi-b-kill-it-in-a-finesse-remix_n_5a4e191de4b06d1621bd69cb?|title=Bruno Mars And Cardi B Kill It In A 'Finesse' Remix For The Ages|last=Dicker|first=Ron|work=[[HuffPost]]|date=January 4, 2018|accessdate=October 7, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191007134409/https://www.huffpost.com/entry/bruno-mars-cardi-b-kill-it-in-a-finesse-remix_n_5a4e191de4b06d1621bd69cb|archive-date=October 7, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Jody Rosen, writing for ''The New York Times'', opined that the single \"sounds like the new jack swing Platonic ideal. It's an imitation so fine-tuned it makes the originals seem ersatz.\"<ref name=\"NYTJR\"/> ''[[The Independent]]''{{'s}} Roisin O'Connor and ''[[Forbes]]''{{'s}} Hugh McIntyre shared a similar opinion, saying that despite being a Bruno Mars song, Cardi B \"steals the show\" due to her perfect and reminiscent of the old-school hip hop flow. O'Connor added that despite the flow, \"it still manages to capture her distinct style\". McIntyre complemented the production and backing vocals, saying it \"could have been a serious smash in the early 90s\".<ref name=\"TIROC\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/hughmcintyre/2018/01/04/bruno-mars-releases-his-song-finesse-with-cardi-b-in-an-attempt-to-make-it-a-hit/#215ce6463ff7|title=Bruno Mars Releases His Song 'Finesse' With Cardi B In An Attempt To Make It A Hit|last=McIntyre|first=Hugh|work=[[Forbes]]|date=January 4, 2018|accessdate=October 7, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180115180126/https://www.forbes.com/sites/hughmcintyre/2018/01/04/bruno-mars-releases-his-song-finesse-with-cardi-b-in-an-attempt-to-make-it-a-hit/#215ce6463ff7|archive-date=January 15, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Accolades===\nThe song was listed by two publications as being among the best songs of the year. On ''Billboard''<nowiki/>'s 100 Best Songs of 2018: Critics' Picks list, the single was placed at number 19. Katie Atkinson wrote that the single \"is best described by its one-word title\". Atkinson added, \"the combination of Mars' nostalgic R&B paired with Cardi's Rosie Perez-channeling swagger was undeniable\".\"<ref name=\"BBBS\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/events/year-in-music-2018/8489483/best-songs-2018-staff-picks|title=Billboard's 100 Best Pop Songs of 2018: Critics' Picks|date=October 7, 2019|work=Billboard|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181212014658/https://www.billboard.com/articles/events/year-in-music-2018/8489483/best-songs-2018-staff-picks|archive-date=December 12, 2018|accessdate=December 11, 2018}}</ref> ''Slant Magazines''{{'}}s Zachary Hoskins criticize the single's opening as it takes from the \"programmed snare line\" of Bell Biv DeVoe's \"Poison\". Nevertheless, he praised Cardi B's guest verse, and the happiness Mars and Cardi B feel as it can be heard on the outro, \"We got it goin' on / Don't it feel so good to be us?\". Hoskins ranked it number 11 on the list of 25 songs.<ref name=\"SSZH\"/> In the same year, the remix was included on Cardi B's 10 Best Features & Collabs: Critic's Picks. Michael Saponara, who compiled the list, placed it at number three.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8092995/cardi-b-best-features-collabs-top-10|title=Cardi B's 10 Best Features & Collabs: Critic's Picks|last=Saponara|first=Michael|work=Billboard|date=January 8, 2018|accessdate=October 7, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191007142313/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8092995/cardi-b-best-features-collabs-top-10|archive-date=October 7, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, \"Finesse\" was nominated for [[Billboard Music Award for Top R&B Song|Top R&B Song]] at the [[2018 Billboard Music Awards|2018 ''Billboard'' Music Awards]], but lost to Mars' \"[[That's What I Like (Bruno Mars song)|That's What I Like]]\" (2017). It was also nominated for [[BET Award for Best Collaboration|Best Collaboration]] at the [[BET Awards 2018|BET Awards]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/bbma/8456842/billboard-music-awards-2018-winners-list-bbmas|title=Here Are All the Winners From the 2018 Billboard Music Awards|work=Billboard|date=May 20, 2018|accessdate=May 20, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180524084717/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/bbma/8456842/billboard-music-awards-2018-winners-list-bbmas|archive-date=May 24, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"EWAH\">{{cite web|url=http://ew.com/music/2018/06/24/bet-awards-2018-winners-list/|title=BET Awards 2018: See the full list of winners|last=Hoggatt|first=Aja|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=June 24, 2018|accessdate=August 25, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180805010003/http://ew.com/music/2018/06/24/bet-awards-2018-winners-list/|archive-date=August 5, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> That same year, the song was nominated for Song of the Year and [[MTV Video Music Award for Best Collaboration|Best Collaboration]] at the [[2018 MTV Video Music Awards|MTV Video Music Awards]], as well as for [[Teen Choice Award for Choice Music \u2013 Collaboration|Choice Music: Collaboration]] and [[Teen Choice Award for Choice Music \u2013 R&B/Hip-Hop Song|Choice Music: R&B/Hip-Hop Song]] at the [[2018 Teen Choice Awards]].<ref name=\"VMAS\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/2018-vmas-winners-see-complete-list-1135082/item/video-year-2018-vma-noms-1127258|title=VMAs: Camila Cabello Wins Video of the Year for \"Havana\"; Complete List of Winners|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=August 20, 2018|accessdate=August 21, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180821223106/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/2018-vmas-winners-see-complete-list-1135082/item/video-year-2018-vma-noms-1127258|archive-date=August 21, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/awards/8469754/teen-choice-awards-winners-list-2018|title=Teen Choice Awards Winners 2018: See the Full List|last=Iasimone|first=Ashley|work=Billboard|date=August 12, 2018|accessdate=August 13, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180920163847/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/awards/8469754/teen-choice-awards-winners-list-2018|archive-date=September 20, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> The single received a nomination for [[American Music Award for Collaboration of the Year|Collaboration of the Year]] and an award for [[American Music Award for Favorite Soul/R&B Song|Favorite Soul/R&B Song]] at the [[2018 American Music Awards]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/american-music-awards-full-list-winners-2018-1146665/item/favorite-male-artist-soul-r-b-1142148|title=American Music Awards: Taylor Swift Wins Artist of the Year, Sets New Record|last=Nordyke|first=Kimberly|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=October 9, 2018|accessdate=October 9, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190526131912/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/american-music-awards-full-list-winners-2018-1146665/item/favorite-male-artist-soul-r-b-1142148|archive-date=May 26, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> In late 2018, \"Finesse\" received nominations for [[Soul Train Music Award for Best Song of the Year|Song of the Year]], [[Soul Train Music Award for The Ashford & Simpson Songwriter's Award|The Ashford & Simpson Songwriter's Award]] and [[Soul Train Music Award for Best Collaboration|Best Collaboration Performance]] at the [[2018 Soul Train Music Awards]].<ref name=\"XXLTMC\">{{cite web|url=http://www.xxlmag.com/news/2018/11/drake-lecrae-and-cardi-b-win-at-2018-soul-train-awards/|title=Drake, Lecrae and Cardi B Win at 2018 Soul Train Music Awards|last=Centero|first=Tony M.|work=XXL|date=November 26, 2018|accessdate=December 1, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181201192336/http://www.xxlmag.com/news/2018/11/drake-lecrae-and-cardi-b-win-at-2018-soul-train-awards/|archive-date=December 1, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019, the track received a nomination for Best International Song at the [[Gaffa (magazine)|Danish GAFFA Awards]], while being nominated for R&B Song of the Year and winning Best Collaboration at the [[2019 iHeartRadio Music Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gaffa.dk/nyhed/135917/gaffa-prisen-og-vinderne-er|title=GAFFA-Prisen: Og vinderne er...|last=Rosenstand Svidt|first=Ole|language=danish|work=[[Gaffa (magazine)|Gaffa]]|date=March 8, 2019|accessdate=June 20, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190901002028/https://gaffa.dk/nyhed/135917/gaffa-prisen-og-vinderne-er|archive-date=September 1, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"BBDW\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/awards/8502606/heartradio-music-awards-2019-winners-list|title=Here Are All the Winners From the iHeartRadio Music Awards 2019|last=Warner|first=Denise|work=Billboard|date=March 14, 2019|accessdate=March 15, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190329082125/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/awards/8502606/heartradio-music-awards-2019-winners-list|archive-date=March 29, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> That same year, the track received a nomination for [[NAACP Image Award for Outstanding Song|Outstanding Song, Contemporary]] category and [[NAACP Image Award for Outstanding Duo or Group|Outstanding Duo, Group or Collaboration]] at the [[50th NAACP Image Awards|2019 NAACP Image Awards]].<ref name=\"THRS\">{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/2019-naacp-image-awards-winners-complete-list-1191277/|title=NAACP Awards: 'Black-ish,' 'Black Panther' Top Winners List|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=March 30, 2019|accessdate=March 30, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190331062137/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/2019-naacp-image-awards-winners-complete-list-1191277|archivedate=March 31, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Commercial performance==\n===North America===\nFollowing the release of the remix and its official music video on January 4, 2018, \"Finesse\" debuted at number 35 on the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] for the week of January 13, 2019. It entered the ''Billboard'' [[Digital Songs]] chart at number 13 with 30,000 copies in just one day of sales. The song had drawn 8.7 million streams from the time of its release, and debuted at the ''Billboard'' [[Hot 100 Airplay (Radio Songs)|Radio Songs]] chart at number 49 with 26 million audience impressions.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8093343/bruno-mars-cardi-b-finesse-remix-hot-100-debut-top-40|title=Bruno Mars & Cardi B's 'Finesse' Remix Flies Onto Billboard Hot 100 in Top 40|last=Trust|first=Gary|work=Billboard|date=January 9, 2018|accessdate=October 20, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180109195909/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8093343/bruno-mars-cardi-b-finesse-remix-hot-100-debut-top-40|archivedate=January 9, 2019}}</ref> After its first complete tracking week, \"Finesse\" peaked at number three on the Hot 100, becoming Mars' 15th and Cardi B's fourth top ten single on the chart. It sold 87,000 copies, peaking at number two on the ''Billboard'' Digital Songs; the song rose 37 places to number 12 on the US Radio Songs chart with 52 million audience impressions and debuted at number one on the [[Streaming Songs]] chart with 38.3 million US streams.<ref name=\"BBGT\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8094379/ed-sheeran-bruno-mars-cardi-b-justin-timberlake-hot-100-top-10|title=Ed Sheeran's 'Perfect' Rules Hot 100, Bruno Mars & Cardi B's 'Finesse' Flies to No. 3 & Justin Timberlake's 'Filthy' Debuts at No. 9|last=Trust|first=Gary|work=Billboard|accessdate=January 16, 2018|date=January 16, 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190405023310/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8094379/ed-sheeran-bruno-mars-cardi-b-justin-timberlake-hot-100-top-10|archivedate=April 5, 2019}}</ref> It also peaked at number one on the US [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs]] chart and was Mars' first single, as a lead artist, to top reach the top of the US [[Dance Club Songs]] chart.<ref name=\"R&BHH\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8238680/bruno-mars-cardi-b-finesse-dance-club-songs|title=Bruno Mars & Cardi B's 'Finesse' Flies to No. 1 on Dance Club Songs Chart|last=Murray|first=Gordon|work=Billboard|date=March 8, 2018|accessdate=October 29, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180309052905/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8238680/bruno-mars-cardi-b-finesse-dance-club-songs|archivedate=March 9, 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe single made Mars' became the second male artist, after [[Lionel Richie]], to have three top-tens from each of his first three studio albums.<ref name=\"BBGT\"/> When the track topped the ''Billboard'' Radio Songs chart, it became Mars' eight number one on the chart, making him the first male artist with eight number one songs. At the time, Rihanna led the list with 13 songs peaking at number one on the chart.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8240981/bruno-mars-cardi-b-usher-finesse-radio-songs|title=Bruno Mars Passes Usher for Most Radio Songs No. 1s Among Males, Thanks to 'Finesse' With Cardi B|first=Gary|last=Trust|work=Billboard|date=March 12, 2018|accessdate=March 12, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180313015223/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8240981/bruno-mars-cardi-b-usher-finesse-radio-songs|archive-date=March 13, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> \"Finesse\" also peaked at number one on the ''Billboard'' [[Mainstream Top 40|Mainstream Top 40]], with Mars becoming the first solo male artist in the chart's history to have nine number ones.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8260894/bruno-mars-cardi-b-finesse-pop-songs-airplay-chart|title=Bruno Mars & Cardi B's 'Finesse' Tops Pop Songs Airplay Chart|work=Billboard|last=Trust|first=Gary|date=March 26, 2018|accessdate=March 27, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180330195759/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8260894/bruno-mars-cardi-b-finesse-pop-songs-airplay-chart|archive-date=March 30, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> \"Finesse\" was certified four times platinum by the [[Recording Industry Association of America]] (RIAA).<ref name=\"RIAA\"/> In Canada, \"Finesse\" peaked at number three on the [[Canadian Hot 100]].<ref name=\"CHOT100\"/> It topped the [[Canada CHR/Top 40]] and entered at nunber three on the [[Canada Hot AC]].<ref name=\"CTOP40\"/><ref name=\"CHOTAC\"/>\n\n===International===\nFollowing the album's release, \"Finesse\" debuted at number 199 on the French single chart for the week of November 26, 2016. At the time of the remix release, the solo version peaked at number 13, being certified gold by the same organization.<ref name=\"FRA\"/><ref name=\"SNEP\"/> In the United Kingdom, \"Finesse\" entered the [[UK Singles Chart]] at number seven, marking Mars' eleventh and Cardi B's first top ten in the country. The following week, the song rose to number five, becoming Mars' highest peak since \"[[24K Magic (song)|24K Magic]]\" (2016), matching the same position. \"Finesse\" remained within the top ten for six consecutive weeks and was certified platinum by the [[British Phonographic Industry]] (BPI).<ref name=\"UK\"/><ref name=\"BPI\"/> On the Belgian charts, the single debuted at number 36 on January 13, 2018 on the [[Ultratop|Ultratop 50]] in Flanders, peaking at number eight for three non-consecutive weeks.<ref name=\"Fla\"/> On the Ultratop 50 in Wallonia, the song entered at number 44 on January 20, 2018, and went on to peak at number eight in March, of that year, for two consecutive weeks.<ref name=\"Wal\"/> It was certified gold by the [[Belgian Entertainment Association]] (BEA).<ref name=\"BEA\"/> Elsewhere, the track topped the charts in Croatia and it peaked at number five on the [[Irish Singles Chart]], spending 24 weeks on the latter chart.<ref name=\"HRT\"/><ref name=\"Ire\"/>\n\nThe remix of \"Finesse\" also peaked at number eight on the Portuguese Singles Chart.<ref name=\"Por\"/> It shipped 10,000 copies, earning a gold plaque from the [[Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Fonogr\u00e1fica Portuguesa]] (AFP).<ref name=\"AFP\"/> It entered the [[Official New Zealand Music Chart]] at number nine on January 15, 2019. In its fifth week, the track peaked at number two, where it remained for two weeks, becoming Mars' sixteenth top-ten single in New Zealand.<ref name=\"NZ\"/> The song received a platinum certification from the [[Recording Industry Association of New Zealand]] (RMNZ), denoting sales of 30,000 copies.<ref name=\"RMNZ\"/> In Australia, the single debuted at number 15 on the [[ARIA Singles Chart]] for the week of January 21, 2018. In its fourth week on the chart, the song peaked at number six for two consecutive weeks.<ref name=\"AUS\"/> It was certified three-times platinum by the [[Australian Recording Industry Association]] (ARIA), shipping 210,000 copies.<ref name=\"ARIA\"/> The song reached the top ten in several other countries, including Greece, El Salvador, and the Netherlands.<ref name=\"Gre\"/><ref name=\"El Salvador\"/><ref name=\"Net\"/>\n\n==Music video==\n===Background and concept===\nThe concept for the music video begun when Mars and Phil Tayag of the [[Jabbawockeez]] were exchanging ideas, always having consideration for the 1990s song vibe. At one point, Mars asked Tayag, \"What if we do ''[[In Living Color]]''?\". Tayag was found of the idea and they decided to go ahead with it.<ref name=\"BBWH\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8093757/phil-tayag-bruno-mars-choreographer-finesse-remix|title=Phil Tayag of the Jabbawockeez Talks Working on the 'Finesse' Remix Video and Calls Cardi B a 'Good-Ass Person'|last=Hussein|first=Wandera|work=Billboard|accessdate=January 16, 2018|date=January 10, 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180110230739/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8093757/phil-tayag-bruno-mars-choreographer-finesse-remix|archivedate=January 10, 2018}}</ref> Afterwards, Mars got the permission and help from [[Fox Studios]] and series creator [[Keenen Ivory Wayans]] to pay homage to the American sketch comedy television series ''[[In Living Color]]'' (1990\u20131994), thanking both of them for it.<ref name=\"TIROC\">{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/news/finesse-video-cardi-b-bruno-mars-watch-in-living-color-grammy-awards-2018-nominations-best-record-a8141006.html|title=Cardi B and Bruno Mars share retro video for 'Finesse' remix|last=O'Connor|first=Roisin|work=[[The Independent]]|date=January 4, 2018|accessdate=November 2, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191007134410/https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/news/finesse-video-cardi-b-bruno-mars-watch-in-living-color-grammy-awards-2018-nominations-best-record-a8141006.html|archive-date=October 7, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Tayag invited [[Danielle Polanco]], Bianca Brewton, TJ Lewis, and Ysabelle Capitul\u00e9 to be dancers for the music video and confessed that the shooting day was a celebration of everyone's accomplishments, \"It wasn't any funny stuff, it wasn't all Hollywood.\" [[DJ Rashida]] made an appearance as one of several DJs on set.<ref name=\"BBWH\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.soulbounce.com/2018/01/bruno-mars-cardi-b-finesse-video/|title=Bruno Mars & Cardi B Are Dripping In '90s 'Finesse'|author=Ivory|work=SoulBounce|date=January 4, 2018|accessdate=May 29, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180524082345/http://www.soulbounce.com/2018/01/bruno-mars-cardi-b-finesse-video/|archive-date=May 24, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Once on the set of ''In Living Color'', trying to replicate it, the dancers felt everything was \"surreal\" with the verbatim, the vibe, the gear, and the clothes.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mtv.ca/how-bruno-mars-and-cardi-bs-finesse-choreography-came-alive/|title=How bruno mars and cardi b's 'finesse' choreography came alive|last=Holmes|first=Charles|publisher=MTV News|date=January 11, 2018|accessdate=November 2, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191007203442/https://www.mtv.ca/how-bruno-mars-and-cardi-bs-finesse-choreography-came-alive/|archive-date=October 7, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nCapitul\u00e9 recalled the music video taking three days to make, consisting of two nine-hour rehearsals and one 15-hour shoot. She added that with Mars they had to work hard, but there were moments of goofiness, and the latter was not looking to be the main character supported by backed up dancers, but instead \"wanted it to feel as if they were all in one crew together\". She said it was an honor for the dancers \"to emulate the show's iconic Fly Girls\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dancespirit.com/dance-in-music-video-2552445276.html|title=What It's Really Like to Dance in a Music Video|last=Randall|first=Kaylee|work=[[Dance Magazine|Dance Spirit]]|date=March 26, 2018|accessdate=November 2, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180329102208/http://www.dancespirit.com/dance-in-music-video-2552445276.html|archive-date=March 29, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> The visual was directed by Mars and Florent Dechard, with choreography done by Tayag and Mars, with Tayag as a creative consultant.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.studiodaily.com/2018/02/bruno-mars-cardi-b-finesse-remix/|title=Bruno Mars and Cardi B: Finesse (Remix)|last=Frazer|first=Bryant|work=Studio Daily|date=February 6, 2018|accessdate=November 2, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181014233146/http://www.studiodaily.com/2018/02/bruno-mars-cardi-b-finesse-remix/|archive-date=October 14, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> According to comedian and former actor of ''In Living Color'', [[David Alan Grier]], the set-up of the video matched exactly the one in the show, including the original paint can intro and the DJ booth.<ref name=\"TFMT\">{{cite web|url=https://www.thefader.com/2018/01/04/david-alan-grier-bruno-mars-cardi-b-finesse-video|title=David Alan Grier on Bruno Mars and Cardi B's \"Finesse\" video aka the perfect In Living Color tribute|last=Tanzer|first=Myles|work=The Fader|date=January 4, 2018|accessdate=November 2, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190408124233/http://www.thefader.com/2018/01/04/david-alan-grier-bruno-mars-cardi-b-finesse-video|archive-date=April 8, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Synopsis===\nThe video premiered on January 4, 2018, and pays homage to ''In Living Color''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/watch-cardi-b-and-bruno-mars-go-full-in-living-color-in-new-finesse-video/|title=Watch Cardi B and Bruno Mars Go Full \"In Living Color\" in New \"Finesse\" Video|last=Kim|first=Michelle|work=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|date=January 4, 2018|accessdate=January 4, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180104192446/https://pitchfork.com/news/watch-cardi-b-and-bruno-mars-go-full-in-living-color-in-new-finesse-video/|archive-date=January 4, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> The former was formatted in a 4:3 aspect ratio, but the main dance sequence was shot at 60 [[Frame rate|frames per second]]. Jake Rodkin, game designer and video editor, explained that this was done in order to evoke the nostalgia of videos shot in the 1990s without using fake scan lines or [[VHS]] fuzz.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://digg.com/2018/finesse-bruno-mars-cardi-b-framerate|title=The New Bruno Mars Music Video Is A Throwback In A Way You Might Have Missed|publisher=[[Digg]]|date=January 4, 2018|accessdate=June 4, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180609154820/http://digg.com/2018/finesse-bruno-mars-cardi-b-framerate|archive-date=June 9, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> The outfits were inspired by brand the [[Cross Colours]].<ref name=\"BBC\">{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/newsbeat/article/42566835/how-bruno-mars-new-music-video-is-a-tribute-to-90s-style|title=How Bruno Mars' new music video is a tribute to 80s style|last1=Moore|first1=Hannah|last2=Mosanya|first2=Lola|publisher=BBC|date=January 5, 2018|accessdate=January 6, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180105224522/http://www.bbc.co.uk/newsbeat/article/42566835/how-bruno-mars-new-music-video-is-a-tribute-to-90s-style|archive-date=January 5, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Cardi B was dressed in washed denim cutoffs, a bold neon jacket, tube socks, a backwards baseball cap, oversized gold doorknocker earrings, and bold pink eye shadow. Mars and the male dancers wore vertical-striped tops and denim cloths, while the female dancers wore crop tops, vertical stripes and bold colors.<ref name=\"TCC\">{{cite web|url=https://www.today.com/style/bruno-mars-finesse-music-video-90s-fashion-heaven-t120805|title=Bruno Mars wears the best of '90s fashion in latest video|last=Callahan|first=Chrissy|work=[[Today (American TV program)|Today]]|date=January 4, 2018|accessdate=November 2, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180115090404/https://www.today.com/style/bruno-mars-finesse-music-video-90s-fashion-heaven-t120805|archive-date=January 15, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"BBBG\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/events/year-in-music-2018/8491545/best-music-videos-2018-top-50|title=The 50 Best Music Videos of 2018: Critics' Picks|work=Billboard|date=December 26, 2018|accessdate=November 2, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190612180426/https://www.billboard.com/articles/events/year-in-music-2018/8491545/best-music-videos-2018-top-50|archive-date=June 12, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The music video opens with Mars and Cardi B using paint and spray paint, reenacting the intro scene from the ''In Living Color'' theme song as the latter raps, before Mars' first verse begins. It features several scenes of old-school choreographed dancing between Mars and a dance troupe similar to the original show's [[In Living Color#The Fly Girls|Fly Girls]], who dance on a rooftop set in a soundstage while Mars sings the second verse.<ref name=\"RSAL\"/><ref name=\"BBBG\"/><ref name=\"EWML\">{{cite web|url=https://ew.com/music/2018/01/03/cardi-b-bruno-mars-finesse/|title=Cardi B and Bruno Mars drop 'Finesse' \u2014 listen now!|last=Lenker|first=Maureen|date=January 4, 2018|work=Entertainment Weekly|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191007134406/https://ew.com/music/2018/01/03/cardi-b-bruno-mars-finesse/|archive-date=October 7, 2019|accessdate=October 7, 2019}}</ref> DJ Rashida is seen in various scenes of the video on a DJ booth.<ref name=\"TFMT\"/><ref name=\"TCC\"/>\n\n===Reception===\nRoisin O'Connor, music correspondent for ''The Independent,'' classified Mars' and Cardi B's tribute to ''In Living Color'' as \"brilliant\".<ref name=\"TIROC\"/> ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]''{{'s}} Raise Bruner said, \"Cardi B and Bruno Mars made the \"splashiest '90s music video.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://time.com/5087739/cardi-b-bruno-mars-finesse/|title=Cardi B and Bruno Mars Made the Splashiest '90s Music Video|last=Bruner|first=Raisa|work=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]|date=January 4, 2019|accessdate=November 2, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190423184716/http://time.com/5087739/cardi-b-bruno-mars-finesse/|archive-date=April 23, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Dicker praised their outfits and energy on the music video.<ref name=\"HPRD\"/> Shenequa Golding, writing for ''[[Vibe (magazine)|Vibe]],'' found the outfits on the homage to be \"jiggy\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vibe.com/2018/01/bruno-mars-cardi-b-finesse-music-video|title=Bruno Mars & Cardi B Pay Homage To 'In Living Color' With The \"Finesse (Remix)\" Video|last=Golding|first=Shenequa|work=[[Vibe (magazine)|Vibe]]|date=January 4, 2019|accessdate=November 2, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180926142940/https://www.vibe.com/2018/01/bruno-mars-cardi-b-finesse-music-video/|archive-date=September 26, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Frank Guan from [[Vulture.com]] criticized Mars for not being innovative due to the video being in tribute to ''In Living Color'', but praised Cardi B's playful and goofiness social-media presence, as it fits \"the early-'90s aesthetic lovingly re-created by Mars\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vulture.com/2018/01/cardi-b-is-perfect-for-bruno-mars-finesse-video.html|title=Cardi B Is Perfect for Bruno Mars's 'Finesse' Video in More Ways Than One|last=Guan|first=Frank|publisher=[[Vulture.com]]|date=January 4, 2019|accessdate=November 2, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180916025418/http://www.vulture.com/2018/01/cardi-b-is-perfect-for-bruno-mars-finesse-video.html|archive-date=September 16, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Several cast members of the TV show, including [[Damon Wayans]], [[Marlon Wayans]], [[Kim Wayans]], Grier, and [[Jennifer Lopez]], praised and thanked Mars for the tribute.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vibe.com/2018/01/damon-wayans-bruno-mars-finesse-video-reaction|title=Damon Wayans Gives Bruno Mars' \"Finesse\" Video A Stamp Of Approval|last=Thompson|first=Desire|work=Vibe|date=January 4, 2019|accessdate=November 2, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180726075922/https://www.vibe.com/2018/01/damon-wayans-bruno-mars-finesse-video-reaction/|archive-date=July 26, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"100GMV\"/>\n\nThe music video for \"Finesse\" was listed tenth on ''Billboard''<nowiki/>'s 50 Music Videos of 2018: Billboard Staff Picks list.<ref name=\"BBBG\"/> In late 2018, Lyndsey Parker of [[Yahoo! Music]] considered the visuals the sixth-best of the year. Parker commented, \"Bruno and his Fly Girl sidekick bring '90s-retro finesse back to the TV screen in this spot-on perfect ''In Living Color'' homage.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sg.news.yahoo.com/20-best-music-videos-2018-180327584.html|title=The 20 best music videos of 2018|last=Parker|first=Lyndsey|work=[[Yahoo! Music]]|date=December 26, 2018|accessdate=November 2, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190624231343/https://sg.news.yahoo.com/20-best-music-videos-2018-180327584.html|archive-date=June 24, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Mike Nied from [[Idolator (website)|Idolator]], on his July list of The 30 Best Music Videos Of 2018 (So Far), ranked the music video at number ten, saying \"The twosome single-handedly brought the '90s back to life in their vibrant collaboration.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.idolator.com/7682377/best-music-videos-first-half-2018?|title=From \"APESHIT\" to \"Fake Love\", The 30 Best Music Videos Of 2018 (So Far)|last=Nied|first=Mike|publisher=Idolator|date=July 9, 2018|accessdate=November 2, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191008065413/http://www.idolator.com/7682377/best-music-videos-first-half-2018|archive-date=October 8, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The video for the song was included on ''Billboard''<nowiki/>'s 100 Greatest Music Videos of the 21st Century: Critics' Picks list. Ranking at number 53, Taylor Weatherby said, \"Just as ''ILC'' was a cultural moment of the '90s, 'Finesse' helped Bruno Mars and Cardi B solidify their place as icons of 2018.\"<ref name=\"100GMV\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/list/8466543/100-greatest-music-videos-of-the-21st-century|title=The 100 Greatest Music Videos of the 21st Century: Critics' Picks|work=Billboard|date=July 24, 2018|accessdate=November 2, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190725042937/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/list/8466543/100-greatest-music-videos-of-the-21st-century|archive-date=July 25, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, the music video won [[Soul Train Music Award for Best Video of the Year|Video of the Year]] at the 2018 Soul Train Music Awards, and was nominated for [[Soul Train Music Award for Best Dance Performance|Best Dance Performance]] at the same award show.<ref name=\"XXLTMC\"/> That same year, it earned earned nominations for Video of the Year at the BET Awards and at the MTV Video Music Awards, as well as both [[MTV Video Music Award for Best Choreography|Best Choreography]] and [[MTV Video Music Award for Best Editing|Best Editing]] at the latter award show.<ref name=\"EWAH\"/><ref name=\"VMAS\"/> The video received the award for Best Music Video at the 2019 iHeartRadio Music Awards and was nominated for [[NAACP Image Award for Outstanding Music Video|Outstanding Music Video/Visual Album]] at the 2019 NAACP Image Awards.<ref name=\"BBDW\"/><ref name=\"THRS\"/> The video received 13 million views within its first two days of release.<ref name=\"BBC\"/>\n\n==Live performances and other usage==\nMars' first televised live performance of \"Finesse\" occurred at the [[Apollo Theater]] alongside the majority of [[24K Magic (album)|''24K Magic'']] (2016) for his [[CBS]] prime time special titled ''[[Bruno Mars: 24K Magic Live at the Apollo]]'', which aired on November 29, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rap-up.com/2017/11/30/video-bruno-mars-24k-magic-live-at-the-apollo-special/|title=Watch Bruno Mars' '24K Magic Live at the Apollo' Special|work=[[Rap-Up]]|date=November 30, 2017|accessdate=January 4, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180105011427/http://www.rap-up.com/2017/11/30/video-bruno-mars-24k-magic-live-at-the-apollo-special/|archive-date=January 5, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Bruno Mars feels the magic|last=Fekadu|first=Mesfin|work=[[Niagara Falls Review]]|location=New York|date=November 29, 2017|via=[[PressReader]]|quote=Mars's energetic dance moves and smooth vocals are at the forefront of Bruno Mars: 24K Magic Live at the Apollo, which debuts Wednesday on CBS. He recorded the special at the Apollo Theater in New York's Harlem, performing the majority of his third album, 24K Magic.}}</ref> He performed the single with Cardi B for the first time at the [[60th Annual Grammy Awards]]. The performance started with Cardi B entering the stage in a color-blocked outfit, while Mars, along with his band and dancers, also wearing colorful outfits, appeared on a separate stage, which had a background featuring the word \"Finesse\" spelled out in the show's logo font. It included a dance break performed by Mars and his dancers to the sound of [[Prince (musician)|Prince]]'s \"[[Gett Off]]\" (1991) and [[House of Pain]]'s \"[[Jump Around]]\" (1992). The live show ended with Cardi B rapping verses of her single, \"[[Bartier Cardi]]\" (2017).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/grammys-2018-watch-bruno-mars-cardi-bs-colorful-finesse-performance-w515868|title=Grammys 2018: Watch Bruno Mars, Cardi B's Colorful 'Finesse' Performance|last=Spanos|first=Brittany|work=Rolling Stone|date=January 29, 2018|accessdate=January 29, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180129034428/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/grammys-2018-watch-bruno-mars-cardi-bs-colorful-finesse-performance-w515868|archive-date=January 29, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/grammys-bruno-mars-cardi-b-give-colorful-performance-finesse-1079461|title=Grammys: Bruno Mars, Cardi B Give Colorful Performance of \"Finesse\"|last=Perez|first=Lexy|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=January 28, 2018|accessdate=October 6, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191006165505/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/grammys-bruno-mars-cardi-b-give-colorful-performance-finesse-1079461|archive-date=October 6, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"BBCP\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/grammys/8096768/grammys-2018-bruno-mars-cardi-b-finesse|title=Watch Bruno Mars & Cardi B Perform 'Finesse' at 2018 Grammy Awards|last=Payne|first=Chris|work=Billboard|date=January 28, 2018|accessdate=October 6, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191005235953/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/grammys/8096768/grammys-2018-bruno-mars-cardi-b-finesse|archive-date=October 5, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The performance received positive reviews, who found it similar to the 1990s theme of the music video.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.spin.com/2018/01/grammys-2018-cardi-b-and-bruno-mars-perform-finesse-remix-video/|title=Grammys 2018: Watch Bruno Mars and Cardi B Perform \"Finesse (Remix)\"|last=Gordon|first=Arielle|work=[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]]|date=January 28, 2018|accessdate=October 6, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191005235951/https://www.spin.com/2018/01/grammys-2018-cardi-b-and-bruno-mars-perform-finesse-remix-video/|archive-date=October 5, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"BBCP\"/><ref name=\"PeopleMP\"/> Chris Payne of ''Billboard'' commented, \"In one of the most captivating moments if the 2018 Grammys combined for an action-packed, '90s-tastic performance.\"<ref name=\"BBCP\"/> Writing for ''Vibe'', J'na Jefferson dubbed the performance as \"stand-out\", while ''[[People (magazine)|People]]''{{'s}} Maria Pasquine wrote, \"The duo, who broke the internet with their ''In Living Color''-inspired video, tore up the Grammys stage.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vibe.com/2018/01/bruno-mars-cardi-b-grammys|title=Bruno Mars And Cardi B Bring Funk And 'Finesse' To Grammys Performance|last=Jefferson|first=J'na|work=Vibe|date=January 28, 2018|accessdate=October 6, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190620084722/https://www.vibe.com/2018/01/bruno-mars-cardi-b-grammys|archive-date=June 20, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"PeopleMP\">{{cite web|url=https://people.com/music/grammys-2018-bruno-mars-cardi-b-finesse-performance/|title=Bruno Mars and Cardi B Dress in '90s Gear to Perform 'Finesse' at the Grammy Awards|last=Pasquini|first=Maria|work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|date=January 28, 2018|accessdate=October 6, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191002014305/https://people.com/music/grammys-2018-bruno-mars-cardi-b-finesse-performance/|archive-date=October 2, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Charles Holmes from [[MTV News]] praised the performance, affirming that \"the chemistry between Cardi and Mars was so electric the duo should think about dropping a collaboration album to save 2018\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/3061076/bruno-mars-cardi-b-finesse-grammy-performance/|title=Cardi B Didn't Win a Grammy, but her \"Finesse \" Performance won the Grammys|last=Holmes|first=Charles|publisher=MTV News|date=January 28, 2018|accessdate=October 6, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191005235953/http://www.mtv.com/news/3061076/bruno-mars-cardi-b-finesse-grammy-performance/|archive-date=October 5, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Cardi B confessed that she was nervous during the performance and decided to use a common stage fright technique in picking a blank spot in the crowd. She said that Mars is a perfectionist, henceforth they rehearsed every day for a whole week, and she didn't want to disappoint him.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8293032/cardi-b-beats-1-interview-invasion-of-privacy|title=9 Takeaways From Cardi B's Beats 1 Interview|last=Honeycutt|first=Shant\u00e9|work=Billboard|date=April 6, 2018|accessdate=October 7, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191007134441/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8293032/cardi-b-beats-1-interview-invasion-of-privacy|archive-date=October 7, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nCardi B opened the 2018 iHeart Music Awards with a medley of her biggest hits, including a verse from the remix of \"Finesse\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/cardi-b-delivers-fierce-hit-medley-at-iheartradio-awards-w517745|title=Watch Cardi B Deliver Fierce Hit Song Medley at iHeartRadio Awards|last=Kreps|first=Daniel|work=Rolling Stone|date=March 12, 2018|accessdate=October 7, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180626083137/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/cardi-b-delivers-fierce-hit-medley-at-iheartradio-awards-w517745|archive-date=June 26, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Hilary Hughes from ''Billboard'' found the performance of the \"Finesse\" remix to have \"shined on its own\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8240366/cardi-b-performance-iheartradio-music-awards-2018|title=Cardi B's 2018 iHeartRadio Music Awards Opening Performance Is One Of Her Best Yet|last=Hughes|first=Hilary|work=Billboard|date=March 11, 2019|accessdate=October 7, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180706080238/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8240366/cardi-b-performance-iheartradio-music-awards-2018|archive-date=July 6, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> On May 20 at the 2018 ''Billboard'' Music Awards, [[Kelly Clarkson]] performed a medley of various ''Billboard'' Hot 100 hits during her monologue, including Cardi B's verse from the remix of Mars' \"Finesse\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/bbma/8456910/kelly-clarkson-medley-bbmas|title=Kelly Clarkson Performs a Medley of Kendrick Lamar's 'Humble' & More Hits at the Billboard Music Awards|last=Warner|first=Denise|work=Billboard|date=May 20, 2018|accessdate=May 29, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180524072013/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/bbma/8456910/kelly-clarkson-medley-bbmas|archive-date=May 24, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.spin.com/2018/05/watch-kelly-clarkson-perform-billboard-music-awards-bbma-2018/|title=Watch Kelly Clarkson Honor School Shooting Victims, Perform a Covers Medley at the 2018 Billboard Music Awards|last=Gaca|first=Ana|work=Spin|date=May 20, 2018|accessdate=October 7, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190505081927/https://www.spin.com/2018/05/watch-kelly-clarkson-perform-billboard-music-awards-bbma-2018/|archive-date=May 5, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> On Mars' third worldwide tour, the [[24K Magic World Tour]] (2017\u201318), \"Finesse\" was the opening act of the setlist.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://los40.com/los40/2017/04/04/los40trending/1491290107_039226.html|title=Bruno Mars pase\u00f3 por Madrid su candidatura al trono del pop|last=Paniagua|first=Arturo|publisher=PRISA|language=Spanish|date=4 April 2017|accessdate=18 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190503161653/https://los40.com/los40/2017/04/04/los40trending/1491290107_039226.html|archive-date=3 May 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://blitz.sapo.pt/principal/update/2017-04-05-Ele-e-funk-ele-e-rock-ele-e-um-romantico.-Bruno-Mars-fe-la-bonita-em-Lisboa|title=Ele \u00e9 funk, ele \u00e9 rock, ele \u00e9 um rom\u00e2ntico. Bruno Mars f\u00ea-la bonita em Lisboa|last=Guerra|first=Lu\u00eds|work=[[Blitz (magazine)|Blitz]]|language=Portuguese|date=5 April 2017|accessdate=18 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170408083206/http://blitz.sapo.pt/principal/update/2017-04-05-Ele-e-funk-ele-e-rock-ele-e-um-romantico.-Bruno-Mars-fe-la-bonita-em-Lisboa|archive-date=8 April 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> ''[[Paste (magazine)|Paste]]''{{'s}} Ellen Johnson considered the performance at the Grammys one of the best of all time, ranking it at number seven, saying that the nostalgia along with Mars' charisma and Cardi B's personable rapping couldn't go wrong.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pastemagazine.com/articles/2019/02/the-best-grammys-performances-of-all-time.html|title=The Best Grammys Performances of All Time|last=Johnson|first=Ellen|work=[[Paste (magazine)|Paste]]|date=February 8, 2019|accessdate=October 7, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191007134756/https://www.pastemagazine.com/articles/2019/02/the-best-grammys-performances-of-all-time.html|archive-date=October 7, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Pentatonix]], an American a cappella group, recorded a cover of the single for their 2018 album ''[[PTX Presents: Top Pop, Vol. I]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/ptx-presents-top-pop-vol-i/1354661995|title=PTX Presents: Top Pop, Vol. I by Pentatonix|publisher=[[iTunes]]|date=April 13, 2018|accessdate=October 13, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191013131536/https://music.apple.com/us/album/ptx-presents-top-pop-vol-i/1354661995|archive-date=October 13, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> It was part of the soundtracks for the video games ''[[Just Dance 2019]]'' and ''[[NBA 2K19]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2018/06/11/e3-2018-just-dance-2019-announced|title=E3 2018: Just Dance 2019 Announce...and It's Still Coming to the WII|last=Dornbush|first=Jonathon|publisher=[[IGN]]|date=June 11, 2018|accessdate=October 13, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181017040422/https://www.ign.com/articles/2018/06/11/e3-2018-just-dance-2019-announced|archive-date=October 17, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newsweek.com/nba-2k19-soundtrack-release-spotify-tracklist-mix-travis-scott-1075334|title='NBA 2K19' Soundtrackd Release on Spotify with Tracklist Mixed by Travis Scott|last=Groux|first=Christopher|work=[[Newsweek]]|date=August 15, 2018|accessdate=October 13, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190812012314/https://www.newsweek.com/nba-2k19-soundtrack-release-spotify-tracklist-mix-travis-scott-1075334|archive-date=August 12, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The remix was also used as the background music for the swimsuit competition of [[Miss Universe 2018]], which was held in Bangkok, Thailand in December of that year.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tg5f5gwBTTE|title=Miss Universe 2018 - Swimsuit Competition|via=[[YouTube]]|date=December 18, 2018|accessdate=November 2, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n| headline = Digital download<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/finesse-remix-feat-cardi-b-single/1328526390?app=itunes&ign-mpt=uo%3D4|title=Finesse (Remix) [feat. Cardi B] \u2013 Single|publisher=iTunes|accessdate=January 4, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180104132527/https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/finesse-remix-feat-cardi-b-single/1328526390?app=itunes&ign-mpt=uo%3D4|archive-date=January 4, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| title1  = Finesse\n| note1 = Remix) (featuring Cardi B\n| length1 = 3:37\n}}\n\n{{Track listing\n| headlin